title: I Am His and He is Mine
author: hannah
text: i am his and he is mine i wonder why he chose me i hear him whispering to my heart i see joy in his forgiveness i want a life filled with his presence i am his and he is mine  i pretend i was actually worthy when all along i never was i feel only his grace can break these chains i touch the scars in his hands i worry for the souls whose love has waxed cold i cry tears of joy when someone forsakes all for him i am his and he is mine  i understand faith is the substance of things hoped for,  the evidence of things not seen i say be not afraid,  only believe i dream of falling into his arms into soul-satisfying rest i try to achieve what he has asked of me i hope my heart is right with him when my time on earth is done i am his and he is mine

title: Generation
author: hunter
text: every generation starts anew young and fresh.  learning from the past to start the future.    each generation grows and shapes the world in their own way,  whether it be peace or war.    every older generation scoffs,   at what is to be their successors.  not knowing how we will change the world.    every generation must prove themselves to the past,   so they can shape the future.   my generation,   the generation of the new.  we get looked down on for being too alone.  we don't talk to each other nearly as much,   and we donâ’t seem worthy to the last generation.  our communication skills are not as good as they once were.  but we the men and women of tomorrow.   are the worlds only hope,   we are the generation of the new.  we will one day prove that we are more than a lit up screen,  because we are the strongest generation to walk this earth yet!

title: The Chance
author: ieasha
text: i think about you all through the day wishing i could have the chance to say,  and if i had the chance to speak so true the first words i'd say would be ''i love you!''        i'd tell you i'm still sad but i'm doing just fine and then i'd tell you how i wish you were still mine,  i'd want you to know i'll always miss you and maybe that's why i feel so blue.            my life has changed since you are now gone my days are so short, and my nights are so long.  i sit here and dream as my eyes are now tears.  remembering our love was promised for years.              i'm sorry our love ended in lies.  why couldn't we say our normal goodbyes?  the way that you left me just broke my heart,  i knew in some way a war had to start.        since you went away my soul seems so dead i wish you were lying with you in our bed holding you tight while you're holding me too,  god how i wish i could still be with you.            you made me laugh when i wanted to cry now somethings not right i have tears in my eyes.                   one more thing i'd want you to see i hope you'll forgive and come back to me,  and i'd want you to know your still in my dreams, i just wish i had the chance to tell you these things.

title: Deserted
author: izbit
text: wandâ’ring worn through shallow lands,  a promise held in melting hands.  a sudden storm in sullen skies,  hides sounds the woeful maiden cries.  the heady heat of desert hills,  which often burns and sometimes kills,  and weighs like tar upon oneâ’s back,  â‘till eyes turn blind as air goes black.  as sand flies swift across the night,  she cowers from the stinging bite.  attempting not to drown in sorrow,   she prays to glimpse the sun of morrow.   her mind is weak,  her body tenses,  she stars to lose hold of her senses.  her hands unfeeling,  numb and slack,  her tongue untasting,  barren,  black.    her ears hear words which none have spoken,  the sunlight beats her body broken.  the maid is close to passing on,  her life bequeathed to hazy dawn.  when suddenly; cold fingertips brush soft against her calloused lips,  and then a mouth replaces these.  a stranger whispers,  pleading,  â“please,  stay strong,  revive,  start life anew,  prevail and i shanâ’t forsake you. â”   and though she is but living dust,  she still can think,  and thinks,  â“i must,  i must go on,  i must survive.  i shall draw breath,  i shall contrive.   a genesis,  a formulation,  an origin,  a new creation.  away foul grime within my lung! begone grim salt beneath my tongue.  iâ’ll overcome you once and all,  prepare no more to laud my fall! with that the maiden mounts to race into a welcome,  safe embrace,  of the man which brought her to believe,  that which you think,  you will achieve.

title: This Path of Ours
author: jacob
text: building in gold to sights unseen,  paths untrod with a shiny sheen; boots untouched and maille unbroken,  mouths still shut with words unspoken.   here i run,  not on my own path,  those that others already hath.  seeking success like few before,   trying to stop the closing door.   cracking the silver to ends too far,  trails too worn with a dusty scar; boots with holes and maille rusted,  mouths still closed with words untrusted.   here i trip,  not on my own path,  those that others already hath.  seeking escape like some before,  trying to stop the closing door.   falling through bronze to depths unknown,  cliffs ruined by crimes unatoned; boots without ground,  maille without hold,  mouths wide open with screams untold.   here i fell,  not off my own path,  those that others already hath.  seeking support like all before,  trying to find the once wide door.

title: I tell myself
author: jacqueline
text: i tell myself that i dont anymore.  again and agian i repeat it to myself.  i never let the world see a glimpse of the truth in my heart.  even though i am sure that it's written all over my face.  i won't admit that i still quiver when he looks at me.  or that  i can still feel his fingers intertwined in mine,  as we held hands.  with all my might i try to hide how a smile comes to my face when he's around.  i won't say  i miss the way he could find my tickles spot.  and how he would laugh,  as i would squirm in his arms.  or the way in a split second,  how with no effort at all he could make me go from crying to laughing.  but the truth is that i do care.  he fills my mind and is always presence in my thoughts.  i face the world with  a smile and say that i am not in love.  i pretend that my heart doesn't break when it's beating or that it doesn't hurt when i breath.  once agian i tell myself that in time all wounds heal.  that he didn't bring something new to my soul.  and that i still don't hungry after it.  i tell myself  i am not  in love.  i tell myself that he's no different from any of my other school girl crushes.  once again i tell myself,  but the question is  how to make myself believe it

text: you've always told me to be brave,  no matter what the case now as i stand here by your grave,  i feel like a disgrace i knew this time would be coming soon,  but yet,  i didn't want to admit it now as i stand here beneath the moon the pain is starting to hit grandma,  why'd you have to leave i never could even say goodbye now i'm left here just to grieve with tears filling up my eyes but i know we will meet again on day,  as for now,  i'll live my life and pray

title: ***Emotions***
author: jennifer
text: crying tears for you longing for someone to hold  on to. . .      just emotions taking  me over    caught up inside  making me seem colder.      the thought of your soft whispers in my ear    telling me sweet things  i wanted to hear.      emotions stuck deep within me     not letting me be the  person i wanted to be.      just the emotions  i wanted to cry out    to hold you and let you know what i'm all about.      hear my cry these emotions i can't hold in any longer    being with you honest that i'm in love    makes me stronger.      longing to hold you to be n your arms    only to be with safe from all harm.      emotions,  if only you could feel what i feel now    in the future hoping we'll be together  somehow.

title: Time to Rest....

title: Withered

title: Slip'

title: I Once Had Thought
author: jessica
text: i once had thought that the world was crshing down on me the harder i tried to keep it stable  the faster it fell  i once had thought that everything had left reality not for better but for worse  i once had thought  that the pain would never stop just the thought of something worse was unbearable  i once had thought that time was my enemy i couldn't make it slow down  or speed up  i once had thought that change was bad i would eventually get used to  the way i am  i once had thought that people were the enemy utterly slefish,  confounded, & arrogant all the same  i once had thought that trust came last didn't need to trust anyone they had no affect on me  i once had thought screaming was something good even though all i got was more anger  i once had thought that i was alone no one to listen  or care  i once had thought  that i would never use the phrase i once had thought

title: The Amazing struggle
author: jessica
text: i walk through the snow.  my skin is pale; my lips are cracked.  out in the emptiness i see nothing.  nothing but white and a small figure.  i cry as the frost bites my face and then. . she takes my place,  my burden.   i am stranded in the desert.  i look at the sun.  my throat is parched; water? i have none.  i see a fountain springing with life,  i reach for it and it runs away;i follow it.  i am then led astray.  she brings it to me,  so real i can feel it,  she gives it to me.   i am out in the ocean,  surrounded by death,  clenching the air,  gasping for breath,  no one is there.  i flail,  but i fail.  i kick and i yell; i'm sinking.  a hand reaches down ans saves me,  she brings me to shore,  no torture,  no more.   there's a pit made by the world,  so black and dreary.  i look,  but don't want.  i fall anyway.  the hands grab me and drag me away.  i feel sick.  i am lost like a lamb,  like a bird fallen from it's nest,  never to be found,  never to rest.   a voice calls for me; a sweet voice that's hers.  i am pulled from the world.  pulled from its curse.  she stays with me.   there was a gap in my heart,  a pit in my soul.  she sewed it up and made me whole again.  tears of joy flow from my face,  my friend is right there staring me in the face.  i stand up and walk,  filled with energy,  as we walk across the sands cheerfully.

title: Cell phone
author: jessica
text: cell phone  my cell phone is pink and it's my favorite color i think.  it is special in so many ways there are so many things to do i can talk on it for days.    numbers will be stored i always have it even as i walk out the door.  it has ring tones that most don't hear they are just silly recordings but i still love to share.    sometimes random numbers call so i just pace and wonder up and down the halls.  my phone is my life i will never let it go without a fight.

title: Some Day...
author: jessica
text: sometimes i feel like nothing goes right,  everyone is mad and in a fight.  they always argue on the phone,  and now i know why mom feels so alone.  my dad has found someone knew,  and deep inside it makes me blue.  sheâ’s very nice in her own little way,  maybe sheâ’ll make my dad happy one day.  she has two daughters younger than me,  being nice is the one true key.  my parents are proud i know they are,  that my sister and i have made it this far,  life will get better like they say,  maybe i can have a perfect family one day.

title: My Friend, My Strength
author: jessica
text: you are my friend,  my strength my comfort zone when i am upset you always calm me with your gentle tone  you laugh when i laugh and cry when i cry if you were not in my life i believe i would die  when i was younger  you were always by my side i needed you with me like a tourist needs a guide  but now i am older  and we have drifted apart but you are still the one i turn to and love with all of my heart  as i go through life i realize you are like not other you are my friend,  my strength you are my grandmother.

title: Running free
author: jessica
text: along the fields their voices are heard.  prancing along to the setting sun's song.  they are joyous and carefree like the world is all theirs running with the wind in their hair with no pains of life to bear.  they are the majestic horses running free among their kind.  they stretch as far as the eye can see and just as beautiful as they could be.

title: Purple skys
author: jessica
text: i go to sleep in purple skys like ripened deep sweet plums where the grass is moist and the air is still and my world is at a place of peace.  like a bodies touch or a warm caress it cradles your life for a moment as i enter this world of silent sleep my dreams unfurl my nature.  this comfortable silence is time for me a time of knowing myself and as life goes on these purple skys will always be just mine.

title: True Love
author: jessica
text: true love is beautiful if it is true you will know  your heart will flutter when you are around him your eyes will stare at him for hours,  fall asleep together on the couch because true love is beautiful.

title: Still Here
author: jessica
text: now,  as i let my feelings go,  you wonder what all i have to show.  but yet i can not express each one,  while some are tiny as the stars,  and others great like the sun.   i tend to hide my emotions inside,  but some of the hurt,  still i can not confide.  my happy memories shall never fade away,  with new ones coming in each day.   as i watch my love float through the air,  so gentle,  soft and sweet,  it warms my heart,  with each and every beat.   and now that you can see how i feel,  maybe one day i can cope and deal,  with the happiness,  and the fear,  that to this day,  keeps me still here.

title: My dog Killer
author: jessica
text: perky ears.  wagging tail.  happy to see you first thing in the morning.  your face covered in loving kisses.  playful and energetic.   chasing leaves blown by the breeze.  playing in the piles of autumn leaves.  loves to cuddle at the most awkward times.  always compassionate and loving.

title: Unending
author: jessica
text: will you tell me how this ends? say that everything's okay.  i've felt more pain now than any other day.  believe me when i tell you forever.   now we know that tomorrow is calling,  and now we know that we can't be together.   where ever life takes me,  you can't be forgotten.  your place in my heart remains forever.  though it's torn and shattered and rotten.  there is hope in my tomorrow regardless.   you've moved on,  and so will i.  after i mourn and grieve and cry.  one day,  my eyes will be dry.

title: Dragon
author: jessica
text: as i enter the moonlit cave the darkness consumes me.  not a human sound is heard.  not a word.  the only thing to guide me is the torch i bare in my hands.  the only thing to hide me is the rocks upon the floor.  i must be silent as a lost soul,  seeking what he could not find.  be warned there are sleeping dragons all around.

title: Summer Days

text: the sun is warm on summer days  the air is in a humid haze,  the grass is green,  and birds will fly on that quiet day when you said,  ''hi''

title: Repelling
author: jessica
text: repelling down and down eyes bigger than the mountain itself,   and a heartbeat faster than the nearby river.   her feet gripped the rusty red stone,   her toes curling,  longing for the safety of the ground.   with each step,   her legs flexed,   pushing them to their limit.   red dust covered her skin,  her clothes,   seeping into the fabric,    from head to toe,   promising to now and forever,   to always be with her.   her lungs burned,   from the fear playing in her brain and the lack of oxygen at 6, 000 feet above sea level.  she longed to be back by the river.   her hands burned,   the beige gloves,  not doing as well of a job as needed,   as the rope seared its way into her palms,  branding her with the memory.   the blue helmet stuck itself to her head,   the sweaty strap chafing at her chin.  the harness hugged her hips,   trying to assure her,   she would be safe.    as she neared the bottom,  her heart rate slowed.  she knew that she would miss this moment.

title: Life and Some Lessons to Be Learned.
author: jessica
text: i've noticed some things in life. . .  weâ’re going to have some heartache and some strife.  lifeâ’s not always peaches and cream,  and everything is not what it seems.   iâ’ve learned youâ’ll never know who your friends are. . .  but your real friends will never stray too far.  sometimes people in life will break your heart. . .  sometimes life will tear you apart.   life and love are just little games of revenge.  there are times when playing these games makes me cringe.  sometimes you think being with him is a real treat. . .  and that he makes your life complete.   but after a while you finally find out. . .  what this boy is really about.  you find out heâ’s not about you. . .  and that he never was being true.   heâ’s just playing a game. . .  and that heâ’s consumed in the fame.  so now heâ’s like forget your emotion.  heâ’s the reason for all the commotion.   soon itâ’ll die down.  baby girl thereâ’s no reason to frown.  life alone is just a phase. . .  soon or later itâ’ll all pass away.

title: Self Image

title: Her Death
author: jewell
text: so still,  in her angelic slumber  with orchid dust on pallid skin  sweet painted lips,  and fingertips  forever locked in clasp and grin.   would she refuse such sweet surrender  to bear the weight of breath  or simply lie,  with her closed eyes  in her soft silken bed of death.   and in her endless world of dream  what remembrance or thought,  or care  are cradled deep,  within her sleep  beyond my reach as she lies there?  and in that moment,  breaking free  is there a sensation of flight  or do we just cease to be  becoming lost within some endless night?

title: You Inflame my Soul
author: jill
text: you inflame my soul with wrath you put my soul in fury and shatter my dreams at your feet like an imperfect pot of clay you say you are genuine to the core,  and yet you rot from the inside out my mouth will tell the anger in my heart once you were of good,  of peace,  of justice,  and now now now you are fraud,  now you are nothing but lies,  folly and deceit your lies you feed are stuffed with sweetness,  and once i indulged,  i breathed no more you you have picked my bones bare of all hope and if my voice is silenced by your oily hand there will be others who will stand and shout and rage at the wrong you have done the untruth that is spread by your fingers,  and while you reap of the unholy sowing i,  in myself,  know no more to you you are a counterfeit coin you are a severer of souls and you rent me from head to groin in one sweep of your scythe which dripped with cunning never again will i fall forward to such malice,  so covered in delight for i know i know who you are

title: Eventually
author: jillian
text: my skies went from beautiful blue to stormy gray not having you around immediately took my sunshine away it makes no sense to me. . . .  it's like your so close,  yet too far away to touch my days go by extremely slow my nights are left to thinking about you constantly the biggest think in my life is always will be you and me i can't wait until the world understands me and then they'll know that you and me were meant to be if they would just sit back and look,  they'll see what we've been talking about there's no doubt in my mind that one day i'll be in your arms again i'm praying to god that you'll be able to way. . . i know i can but for now while were torn in two i'll always remember,  that i'll always love you i ask the lord above that you'll be the one there saying 'i love you too' so keep your head up high  while these endless days pass us by always keep me in your heart,  soul and mind because once the future is totally mine i'll be there waiting for you waiting for the words i love you so please try and forgive the present and get ready for the future for the future holds the greatest things of all. . . .

title: FiNaL
author: jocelyn
text: my favorite thing is tournaments  with my team.  the ones where you stay  in nice hotels.  the fields in the morning are coated  with morning dew.  while the sun is slowly peaking out  over the hills like a child.  the precisely manicured grass.  it is perfect.  running down the field,  you pass the ball.  she shoots.  she scores.  you run up and give her a high five.  the whole team beams with pride.  we are fired up.   hotels.  we run around wild.  just remember stay away  from the lobby.  playing hide and seek tag.  soccer games in the hallways.  lesson learned stay away  from the reception desk.   we are in the final.  we have played this team before.  they were once out for the win.  now they are out for blood.  we are all confused and playing bad.  i watch as she is about  to take a shot.  iâ’m sitting off the bench with excitement.  she scores.  we scream.  1-0.  we are winning.  composed,  that we are.  the time runs out.  we are the champions.  my team and i.  we lift the trophy high.  with our smiling faces  in the reflection.  so proud.  my team.   my family.

title: Crazy Old Men.
author: johanna
text: there once was a crazy old man,  who loved to play in the sand.   but one day at the beach,  he was bit by a leech.   so he screamd,  he cried and he ran.   then he went to the zoo,  and one of the keepers said his bite gave him the creepers,  and not to go back to the beach,  where you got bit by a leech,  while playing in the sand.   so he screamed and he cried and he ran.   then he went to the movies,  because he also loved scooby.   but when he got candy,  this lady named mandy asked about his huge bite.  then when he told her,  ms.  mandy,  who was also older,  said not to go back to the beach,  where he was bit by a leech while playing in the sand.   so he screamed and he cried and he ran.   then he went to the doctor,  where they called him ''mr.  moctor, '' and he was told not to go to the beach where he was bit by a leech,  while playing in the sand.   so he screamed,  he cried and he ran.   then he went to a dinner,  where he asked for a number.   when they came back the old man fell flat on his back,  and the waiter screamed,  cried,  then he ran.

title: Grapes
author: jonah
text: i ran to my room with a handful of grapes,  to dissect them into tiny shapes,  i named them steve they were so sweet,  i knew in a game that they would never cheat,  so when i opened them i found the seeds,  and planted them beside the weeds,  they grew a lot that night,  the seeds and the weeds,  the weeds grew a lot but the seeds did not,  so i put the seeds into a pot,  they formed a heart inside that pot,  and that is where i got,  my new plan to savor my grapes and eat with care,  because in each grape there was a layer,  that's where they kept their heart.

title: Me
author: jonathan
text: me joking around can be good but it also can be bad once you joke around in a very hurtful way then you have to suffer with the chances of losing a friend you like/love.  neither way of joking around is good for you because of the favorite saying â“what goes around comes aroundâ” another reason why joking around can be hurtful is because you might say it to the wrong person at the wrong time there is no way you can stop yourself from doing or saying anything stupid having people say jokes to you won't be as fun as you saying them to someone else after all of the joking is over everyone is either happy or they are frustrated or angry nevertheless it's time to put the joking aside and worry about more important things than hurting other people.

title: Who was that child?
author: jonathan
text: death so near yet so far to us all a child dying of hunger,  that starvation draining his essence his mother running,  crying for help.  but nobody hears her.  or sees her fertile tears running with her.  running,  even with her weakness.  tender waves of emotion flood her as she realises her child is dying.  but she never gives up and keeps holding him forever.   even when she kisses him goodbye she still holds him we sit at home and hear of tragedy in africa but we don't feel the grief of that mother.  then our own child cries for help.  we come rushing to him and find him crying and we hold him like that mother in africa.  we call for help and it comes.  all this over a cut soiled with earth.

title: My love for you
author: jonathan
text: love,  a whip of fire in my heart,  i finally found the someone who,  could break my heart and make it two,  always,  i think of you with an undying affection,  maybe,  a reflection,  of my unbound love for you.  i want,  to hold you in my arms,  kiss you on the lips,  love you in my sleep,  my love,  you make me weep.  a tender goddess in my thoughts,  ensnaring my senses as you walk.   i want to. . . .  wipe the tears falling from your eyes,  save you from pain and suffering in the world,  save you from the tyranny of evil men,  save you from heartbreak.   be your hero forever and a day,  never will i go astray,  be there by your side forever,  my lovers' rope will not be severed. . .

title: Life is Fine
author: jorge
text: i went down to the river,  i set down on the bank.  i tried to think but couldn't,  so i jumped in and sank.   i came up once and hollered! i came up twice and cried! if that water hadn't a-been so cold i might've sunk and died.   but it was cold in that water! it was cold!  i took the elevator sixteen floors above the ground.  i thought about my baby and thought i would jump down.   i stood there and i hollered! i stood there and i cried! if it hadn't a-been so high i might've jumped and died.   but it was high up there! it was high!  so since i'm still here livin',  i guess i will live on.  i could've died for love-- but for livin' i was born  though you may hear me holler,  and you may see me cry-- i'll be dogged,  sweet baby,  if you gonna see me die.   life is fine! fine as wine! life is fine!

title: Wednesdays
author: josh
text: people are eternally waiting.  ''wednesdays are hard, '' they say.  they're the car ride home.  and the change you tell the cashier to keep.  they're the walk to practice.  and the spaces between words on paper.  they're the days you just get through.  and frankly,  we don't have the time to just get through days.  because these days add up.  and life is much too short to spend all week waiting for the weekend.  so be the type of person who can find something to smile about on a wednesday.

title: I don't understand love
author: joshua
text: the greatest feelings i ever had,   came from being with you,  it would have worked out if only i hadn't said,   those three terrible words, ''i love you''  let me tell a story,  of this little boy.  hopefully it won't get too boring,  with the way i speak of his joy.   fifteen years old he was,  never wanted anything for himself.  now comes what was to cause,   that boy to feel full of wealth.   you see he came across a girl,  his life was now great.  his head began to whirl,  he had no reason to hate.   he embarked on his quest,  to gain her heart.  truly he did his best,  but,  he did not know the lover's art.   every moment he spent with her,   he was happy and smiling all the time.  his longing still did endure,  but now there comes sadness to this rhyme.   when he told her how he felt,  she did not return his love.  forever since in fear has he dwelt,  that he would never gain her love.   you see he had not gained her heart,  but lost his own instead.  never again wll he try to play this part,  he is now left wishing he was dead.   the greatest feelings i ever felt,  came from being with you.  it would have worked out if only i hadn't said,  those three terrible words,  ''i love you. title: Black Canvas
author: june
text: stars don't exist in our city.  so when we step outside to look into the sky,  i'm not sure what we're looking for.  we run through the backdoor and find planets in my yard,  but nothing to make wishes on.  we plead we are due for some wishes. . .  still our claims won't turn off the city's lights,  or create cracks in the black canvas tonight.  so drive me to an open field,  away from the bricks and metal.  i will memorize the color of your eyes and create portraits of your harsh features,  that are tattooed within my brain.  i will give you similes absorbing catastrophes,  i will write you another poem about the rain.  just,  in return,  drive me to an open field,  inject your galaxy into my bloodstream,  and i can see it now- it's so beautiful- but it is missing something bright and burning.   i long to see the stars.

title: Down The County Road at 12:00am
author: kaela
text: i donâ’t understand it but i know by any means that itâ’s here to stay.  whether it is a sign of intelligence or ignorance,  i do not know for i am not certain as to my own whereabouts.  but love is here.   ever present in my mind,  fills me with dread and some regret.  but ask me again on a different day and i may compete on the opposite spectrum of things; feeling adrift in a sea of pride and self-belief,  no longer haunted by self-doubt.  the origin of its existence is unexplainable and unbeknownst to me; often appearing unfathomable.  the answer is ever elusive and fills me with great stress and mountains of frustration.  no way to escape it.  time to embrace it.

title: Sleep
author: kaitlyn
text: sleep is not the answer nor will it aid you in finding answers to life,    sleep is the absence of life while we are still alive,   and yet answers may seem to slip away to disappear,    especially when we look closer to try and make them clear,   sleep is our deepest fears,  most hidden secrets,  and most blissful realities,   it is where we ourselves get trapped in our own mind and are victim to our brutalities,   dreams are a form of sleep they fire in our head for what seems like a life time is only really seconds,   but that distorts time,  and maybe that's good,  those are the expectants,   however where does it stop?   when does one dream flip to the next plot?   when you try to remember one dream it's as if all your dreams are in a clot,    but then who would want to open themselves up enough to remember a dream,    just close your eyes and let them pass cause some are not what they seem,    some seem like you're staring into black space,    while others set you in a specific place or displace the absence of interspace,    where only you and your mind are playing a giant game of chess,    and only you can press to deal with the stress,     of you fighting your own mind on a battle field only you can see,    and only when you wake are you truly free

title: Lost
author: karina
text: ever feel like you're alive but not really there? wandering in an empty body full of nothing but air? you become a stranger and you don't know yourself.  hiding behind a fake smile and unable to get out.  you try desperately but fail to gain back some control.  you wind up finding it in the wrong places and dig yourself into a deeper hole.  you just have no passion left to do what you always did well.  nothing is of interest anymore and you feel like you're in hell.  you try to stand up but once again you fall.  it's always the littlest things that make you feel so small.  you have nothing and no one left to care.  and here you are not living but really just there.  so wallow in your saddness,  your anger and your pain.  even though staying there leaves you with nothing left to gain.

title: SuperMan
author: kathryn
text: his eyes are like blue jewels,  that sparkle and shine.  his heart is as pure as gold,  and definitely mine.   he is the one i run to,  when it's all too tough.  he's the soulder i cry on,  when everything's rough.   he's the light in my storm,  and helps me so much.  he can brighten any day,  with one simple touch.   he's the love of my life,  and all that i need.  he's my soul's one true mate,  and i trust his lead.   he's a waterfall of love,  and sent from above.  he's mine and mine forever,  he's my superman.

title: Harmony of Nature
author: kathryn
text: the swollen somber clouds slowly roll in  the sky grows dark and dismal  birds quickly disperse from the vast sky  the wind sweeps through the willow tree  leaves rustling a soft tune  the wind picks up  the sky transforms to a black hole  a trickle of rain hits my face of despair  thunder starts to rumble through the clouds   lightening sparks the sky with brilliant colors  shades of pinks and yellows cover the sky  the tune now louder,  more apparent  with all elements working in harmony   creating and astounding symphony  a smile creeps across my face  for i now see the true beauty of nature

title: Contented
author: kati
text: lounging on the floral bed,   looking healthy and well fed,  the contented dog dozes lightly.   never has there been a dog,  whose bright eyes shown through in a fog,  bright blue pools of wonder  with droopy auburn ears,   stretched out long through the years,  and a tiny chocolate mustache,   under a nose,  slightly damp,  blacker than a power outage through the whole camp.  the dog snuggles down deeper.   his snow white body,  quiet and still,  as if heâ’s never had to face a great thrill,  is beauty to the beholder.

title: Day/night
author: katie
text: night is dark,  there are no birds chirping,  no leaves to be seen floating.  night is quiet.  it leaves me with thoughts,  that day taught me to forget.  it leaves me with questions,  that escape from my mouth like poison.  it leads me to believe that these feelings are wrong,  and i am wrong for wanting anything good to happen.  it tells me my friends are my only foes,  and reminds me that i am alone.  it stays with me until my tears dry and my eyes close.  day greets me hours later,  and birds chirp.  it teaches me to keep busy.  it tells me to forget those questions,  because i am not alone.  everything is okay,   until night comes and reminds me of all those things day taught me to forget.

title: The Grotto
author: katie
text: 45 degrees 05â’n 81 degrees 23â’w northern bruce peninsula.  it was a windy day out on lake huron in late july clear,  blissful,  breathtaking.  you could barely tell where the horizon started and where the water ended.   tall mountains, disturbed water,  luscious trees,  jagged rocks all you could see for miles time just stops when youâ’re out on the lake.  the most amazing part of the entire scene was the hidden cave.   swimming through the freezing water was a breeze the climbing was the hardest part.  the feel of the sharp rocks as i scaled the side of the  slippery cave,  even though it was ominous and creepy i thought onward and upward.   fifteen feet above the water inside the gigantic cave  my feet left the rock as i leapt into the air i could feel the second when my feet hit the deep water at that moment i truly felt alive.

title: Anorexic Girl
author: katie
text: tired of seeing the ''fat'' girl in the mirror,  she breaks the glass.  she has blood on her knuckles,  and scars to last.   she's bitter and angry and her soul is cold.  she won't ever eat,  no matter what she is told.   to her,  life is all about being thin.  ''if i'm not, '' she thinks,  ''then i won't fit in. ''  does fitting in mean ending up in a hospital bed? where at any moment she can wind up dead?  she lays down on the bed with regrets of that night.  she wishes she could've eaten,  to make it all right.   now she's weak and tired,  pathetic's her soul.  ''maybe i must eat something in order to be cool. ''  later that week,  she got out,  she's determined to change.  she wouldn't have been accepted anyway,  ain't that strange?

title: Why?
author: katie
text: why cry if there's no one there to hear? why stay if you want to disappear? why make a promise that you can't keep? why confess secrets if they're too deep?  why live this life if you want to die? why stay grounded if you want to fly? why buy things if they're useless and junk? why eat something if you knew it stunk?  why fight a war if it does no good? why drop bombs in an innocent 'hood? why kill people for no real reason? why do all this in every season?  why?

title: Night of Terror
author: katie
text: she's all alone,  a deserted street.  who know what kind of people she'll meet.   she hears a person,  and sees a gun.  she's worried and too frightened to run.   she decides to stay,  than face a bullet.  she's told to give her purse to some guy with a mullet.   shocked and scared she turns to leave.  she goes to tell anyone who will believe.   she goes home to find peace,  and peace she shall find,  but she can't seem to take that scene out of her mind.   finally,  her boyfriend will come home.  he wanted to tell her not to roam.   too sorry for her,  he holds her tight,  till eventually she'll fall asleep later that night.

title: That's Just Me

text: i do crazy things.  i say nasty jokes.  i sleep all the time.  i hate all people.  i like orange pop.  who cares who i am,  'cause that's just me.

title: Don't Bring Me Down
author: katie
text: a perfect day,   and rainy too.  it can't bring me down. . .   i have a smile,  on my face.  until i am put down.   my loss of hope,  my pleas for an end.  why'd you bring me down?  i don't get it,  why do you do this? you love to see me down.   i've done nothing,  to deserve this.  you do like to see me down.   i already have,  so many problems.  so please don't bring me down!

title: Why Must We Hide?
author: katie
text: why must we hide?  he wears a hat to hide exposed scalp.  she wears make-up to hide her flaws.  he wears ten tons of jewelry to hide his simpleness.  she wears loose shirts to cover her fat.   why must we be someone we're not?

title: No One Likes Her
author: katie
text: you don't like her.  she doesn't like her.  he doesn't like her.  no one likes her. . .      why doesn't anyone like me???

title: Poems
author: katie
text: some poems inspire,  some are desires,  some are your fears,   some bring you to tears.   some poems give hope,  some help you cope,  some bring you peace,  some put you at ease.   some poems are long,  some are written strong,  some are short,  some are like a resort.   all poems are unique,  all poems are neat,  all poems are fun,  this poem is done.

title: Midgets
author: katie
text: i keep midgets in my trunk.  i keep them there all night.  i keep with them an angry skunk.  i love the midgets' fright.

title: Two Towers
author: katie
text: two towers proudly stood.  why they vanished is misunderstood.  we ask ourselves,  ''why?''  suicidal terrorists made two crashes.  now those towers lay in ashes.  we still ask ourselves,  ''why?''  was it jealousy of our rights? when all they have is taliban and fights? and we still ask ourselves,  ''why?''  if they think they are destroying us,  they are wrong.   we stand tall with no fuss.  but we still ask ourselves,  ''why?''  although we may not find a cure,  we know one thing is for sure.  we proudly exclaim,  ''god bless america!''

title: Life
author: katie
text: you don't understand me.  you are all the same.  you cause all the trouble.  why am i to blame?  i don't understand you all.  i don't like your attitude.  i hate this society.  why are you all rude?  life should be so different.  life should have a change.  life should have no troubles.  why is life so strange???

title: A Night to Remember
author: katie
text: ''this would be a night to remember. '' this is what they said.  but no one ever knew,  that they would find her dead.   a pool of blood beside her head,  a gun held in her hand,  a suicidal letter,  by the stage set for the band.   she was ready for this dance.  she was eager to see her date.  but as soon as he arrived,  it was much too late.   there were screams and cries.  she shot some of her friends.  she shot a lot of teachers.  then her life would end.   she was real unhappy.  she did not feel loved.  she felt so unwanted,  now her soul's up above.   this will be hard to forget,  but they only can remember,  that very painful night.  in the middle of december.

title: Hello Bullies
author: katie
text: hello bullies:  i don't care what you say,  i'm beautiful in every way,  so please don't bring me down today.   ~*thanks*~

title: Devils
author: katie
text: devils are so cute and small.  i love that they don't have a flaw.  i love how they don't abide by any law.  i love the way they take my leg and gnaw.  devils are so cute and small.

title: A lonely Soul
author: katie
text: a lonely soul is shoved to the ground. . .   you walk away,  proud.  you don't look back.  you love to see sorrow.  you are truly insane.   a lonely soul cries. . .   you don't hear it.  you don't care.  you act like nothing happened.  you continue walking.   a lonely soul builds up anger.   you don't understand.  you want to hurt this soul again.  you don't like when this soul is happy.  you feel that this soul's sorrow makes you stronger.   a lonely soul plans an escape.   you really don't get it.  you only want to see sorrow.  you hate this soul. . .  but for what??? you know no tolerance.   a lonely soul escapes through poetry.  that lonely soul is me.

title: Peace Wish
author: katie
text: i woke up with a smile on my face.  nothing could bring me down.  but i thought of hungry children in a faraway place,  and i began to frown.   in this land we are all selfish,  so greedy,  full of hate.  if i only had one wish,  it'd be that they already ate.   no more hunger,  no more war,  is what we need to live.  we also need much more,  like learning to forgive.   we need a world peace,  so we can live as one.  our minds can be at ease,  and sorrow can be all done.   we may never make this change,  but the least we can do is try.  do it now,  don't think it's strange,  so you'll go to heaven when you die.

title: My Dream
author: katie
text: here i am,  try and get me.  i am running from you,  try and get me.  you're way back there? where are you? na na na na naaaaaaaaa naa. . . . .  try and get me.  try. . .  try. . .  try. . .  get me.  where are you? try and get me.  . . .  ??? you got me?  [i wake up. ]

title: Day of Hell
author: katie
text: i'm screaming inside.  lost and confused.  you endless torture,  somehow,  keeps you amused.   i ask you why,  but you pick on me more.  how did i deserve this? you say,  ''this is war. . . ''  i'm panicking inside,  but i try to relax.  but it's kinda hard to,  when they tell me harsh facts.   ''you're ugly,  i hate you,  you can go straight to hell. '' but i'm thoroughly pleased,  at the sound of the bell.   i walk quickly away,  with tears in my eyes.  i come home to room,  to have a good cry.

title: Sun
author: katie
text: the sun is bright.  the sun is shining.  make it go away.   it's much too cheery for my sorrow.  make it go away.   i like it dark when i'm alone.  make it go away.   i want the rain to hide my tears.  make it go away.   you take your sun.  i'll be alone.  think i'll hide away.

title: The Girl
author: katie
text: the girl who wondered,  ''why am i here?'' felt people wanted her to disappear.  she lived in sorrow,  pain,  and fear.  always was afraid to shed a tear.   she wanted to go away and hide.  she had no one in which to confide.  she lost her hope,  she lost her pride.  she had no religion,  no spiritual guide.   she grew deeper and deeper into dispair.  and she felt like people didn't even                                    care.  she was paranoid that people just sat                               and stared.  she felt like people made things unfair.   when she sat in her room,  she shut off                                her light.  and she thought of the times when she                           got in a fight.  she thought she was always wrong and                              never right.  she sat and she thought until it was                                    night.   she slept off her pain and some of her                                    grief.  she hoped that then next day would                        bring some relief.  but it all was the same,  to her                                disbelief.  she turned to write angry words on                               loose-leaf.   to her,  nothing ever seemed to change.  she felt like an outsider,  somebody                                  strange.  that day,  her and her enemy had a fight                              to arrange.  punches only is what they'd have to                                 exchange.   but that day it had gone too far.  someone brought in a crow bar.  in defense,  a knife left a scar.  they both were put behind bars.   the girl wondered,  ''why am i here?'' she just wanted to disappear.  she fled prison to jump off a pier.  no more sorrow,  pain,  or fear.

title: About a Boy
author: katie
text: the boys name is lee,   i think he's very sweet.  i like him very much,  but i'm having a second budge we get on very well,  even if it's hell.  i love this boy called lee and i hope he loves me like i can see.

title: She's Watching Me......
author: katie
text: i get a horse from a stall,  sheâ’s watching me,  watching me  i brush the horse so heâ’s shiny,  sheâ’s watching me,  watching me  i put the saddle on the horse,  sheâ’s watching me,  watching me  i put the bridle on the horse,  sheâ’s watching me,  watching me  i take the horse in the arena,  sheâ’s watching me,  watching me  i get on the back on the horse,  sheâ’s watching me,  watching me  i ride the horse through the night,  sheâ’s watching me,  watching me  finally iâ’m done,  so i go to my horse,  and i give her a big squeeze,  i tell her that we are forever,  and that we will never part.   she looks at me with her eyes,  and gives me a soft neigh,  i know that she understands,  that sometimes i canâ’t always be with her.   then i get her bridle,  and put it on her,  then i ride her bare back,  till itâ’s time to go  sheâ’s not watching me any more,  because now iâ’m on her back,  and we are together forever!

title: Thinking Of You
author: kayla
text: as i try to make the day go fast,  so that i can see you fast,  praying to god that we last. i want to be forever in your arms,  and never leave your side.  ive never felt the same with anyone in my past,  so i guess i found something special at last.  to fell this way,  the way i do with you,  is undesirable.  you've made me laugh,  you've made me cry, when you broke my heart,  i thought i was going to die.  ashes for ashes,  dust to dust,  i hope in the future there's still an ''us''.

title: A Poem to my Best Friend
author: kristen
text: even though you are sometimes sad and blue,  that doesn't matter because i will always love you.  and even though we sometimes fight,  you always find a way to brighten up the light.  and when you get tired of me always being there,  i will just stay and get in your hair.  and when you are filling down,  i'll lift you up off the ground.  and even though we haven't had the best relationship,  i still think you are really hip.  when we argue ang when we agree,  it makes us become closer don't you agree? i love you so much that i would take my life for you and die,  but then you would cry.  just remember that whatever god has planned for us two,  it is the best for you.  and even though i may not show everything to you,  that does not mean i don't love you.  so just remember what i say,  that i love you and you are the best friend that anyone could ever have and don't ever go away.

title: My Cat Rascal
author: kristina & kelsey
text: my cat rascal:   green eyes,   some surprise,   little paws,   and twinkling eyes.    kiss on the cheek,   kiss on the nose,   yarn wrapped around,   both little toes.    smiles always,   dimples in cheeks,   chasing her ball,   we'll be laughing for weeks.    scarfing her food,   she's one little pig,   never gets thinner,   but seems to get big.    she sleeps forever,   she always has snored,   she might do it for fun,   when she gets real bored.    looking around,   ''ohh,  where could she be?'',   there in a ball,   in the chair beneath me.    she's gone off to bed,   so cute as she purrs,   we'll leave her alone,   with a dream that is hers.   by: kristina & kelsey.

title: Small things are the Big things
author: kritika
text: small things in life  are often disregarded,   often ignored.  we wait for something large,  looming on the horizon.  while something small,  numerous is already here,  bringing in the real happiness.   a decent breakfast,  a warm sunset,  the smile of someone you love,  or when you find an extra dollar in your pocket.  sunday brunches with your best friends,  a good cup of coffee,  a fresh-smelling flower,  or the smile of a stranger walking past you on the streets.   itâ’s the little things in life  that matter the most.  appreciate what you have.  be grateful.   because one day  you will glance back and discover they were the big things.

title: Rejoice

text: fear cripples down my spine,  whispers and the sound of people crying,  tears drip down my cheek,  shivering,  standing at a narrow cliff,  the horrifying sound of the whisper,  ''who is that i seek?''       the sound of chains gliding the rock,  approaching behind me.  the poorly sound of people mourning in agony . . so rejoice now or forever hold your peace.

title: Bad Day
author: krystle
text: a bad day for him filled with useless efforts.  it seems like the world crumbles beneath his feet every day.  he won't listen to the things i tell him about his acting or his writing or that everything with be okay.  he won't believe that there's good in this world.  easily falling in love,  mourning over every girl until he falls in love again.  he loves each more and more than the last.  he scares me  with the marks on his arm and his pessimism.  i need him to be here.  my friend,  my best friend can't leave me alone.  i trust him against all warning.  i wish he'd trust me.  i see where he can and will be: on broadway,  singing showtunes.  at the globe theater,  saying ''good-bye,  ancient lady!'' in nyc,  signing books.  or at the academies,  saying his acceptance speech.   but he doesn't see what i see; i see opportunity. . .  he sees another bad day.

title: Wicked Fairies
author: kymberly
text: wicked fairies dance in the swift moonlight,  as they prance deeply on the rose colored trees filled with cotton flowered seeds.   orange pink,  and green,  petal dresses,  swaying heavenly through the bright moonlight beam.   singing like the wind,  echoing in the breeze,  leaping on the gorgeous trees.   their dark luscious hair flying through the crisp wood air,  while their small little bodies chase eachother in despair.   laughing and playing in the frosty river bay,  while they talk and lay on a hallow lingering log.   as the fog thickens the delicate tiny fairies fly away,  till the next chilly day.

title: Banana and Peanut Butter
author: larissa
text: almost every afternoon,   i go home,  and fill my stomach with odds and ins around the kitchen quietly i make the rounds,  from pantry to fridge,  looking like a bafoon,  scoping out my prey like a zebra going after whatever zebras eat in the wild.   my prey usually turns out to be a ripe brown speckeled banana,  with a taste,  quite mild,  lathered with brown gooey organic peanut butter (those hydrogenated oils in unnatural butters make me shutter) i eat this concoction at night after i get home from here or there always with a cheer oh,  sometimes on whole wheat toast i enjoy the mixture on quite a lot although iâ’ve never tried to roast wait,  yes yes i did give it a shot while in the woods this summer i didnâ’t want a graham cracker smothered in chocolate so onto the fire went the banana  warm and mmm kabama it truly hits the spot on cold 43 degree evenings buried up in the mountains sometimes,  i get lazy about this scrumptious snack i just layer with a spoon and place it on top each bite donâ’t try to pack the mushy mixture for it might ruin your book back and the banana can get brown and bruised and that is when the gooey glob starts to lack the magic and feeling in your stomach that says â“iâ’m packedâ”.

title: Full Bloomed
author: lashona
text: as delicate as a rose,  i can be,  also,  painful as a thorn,  that sticks you from a tree.  many sides there are to this one being,  although all at once,  they've never been seen.  i know that at a short glance you would not believe,  but my infectious personality at first makes it hard not to receive me.  i can be reassuring for a moment and doubtful in the next,  most try to triger each side,  but they can't even if it's with their best.  i try not to be so hostile in their sight,  but just being around some,  makes good things seem not right.  all these emotions are stored deep inside,  hidden from the world until i start to cry.  then when the tears come,  they will all realise,  that the world is portrayed as hell from my eyes.  and when i confess and become intuned,  i shall be ready and declared full bloomed.

title: Not until he was Gone
author: lashona
text: he lived his life,  one day at a time,  he worked for no man,  he just tried to stay alive.  he came upon many stumbling stones,  but held his own weight,  he was responsible for his own.  even though he was responsible and such,  his life went unnoticed,  no one's hand had he ever touched.  though no hand was touchedby his,  he made it his goal,  to help all he came in contact with.  the reward that he reaped was oh so sweet and just so right,  but only to be received when he was banned from the world one night.  and now his work,  though minute in frame,  is now being treasured,  though never to be performed by him again.

text: who is that?  a gravel and glass shadow  of big brown eyes and unkempt hair  pierced ears,  two lips  barely there  tan lines still showing   in january though the spf.   and those hands:  small and calloused and ink-stained  paper cuts still bleeding at the knuckles  and dirt  i can never keep my nails clean.   when did my hips grow so much?  and the scar on my leg faded…  i faded  into a reflective double dimension.

title: Nonsense
author: lexi
text: so now my dear,  on this cold and dreadful dawn,  here i sit with you in my heart.  iâ’ve bled a path for the lonely.  iâ’ve marked scares on all their faces,  not only to watch them die while i bind blades with laces.  nonsense fills my cup as i pore it over.  the liquid poison kisses my lips but i,  lost in the abyss of dreams of blood and gore,  notice not.  words escape my mouth,  but alast,  i speak nothing.  for nothing is all there is in this circle of my being.  nothing and nonsense.  so i dock my ship on the shore of your arms an entwined will i be,  for never have i touched hands with such feeling before.  itâ’s nice…

title: Eyes
author: liam
text: \tmy dad and i have the same dark brown eyes like chocolate.  small,  in the shape of an o letter with a little,  almost invisible,  refinement in the sides of the eye.   even our eye browses are a lot alike.  i wish i would have had his perfect view.  he sees through a clean almost shinny glass,  and i see through a broken dirty glass.  without any glasses iâ’m almost a blind old woman walking insecurely down the street.    i wish i could have his perfect view about life.  what his eyes saw could never be what my eyes will see.  from birth to death and from happiness to grief.   he has sad eyes.  i have never had the courage to ask why.  sometimes,  i see his happy eyes too.  and when i do,  i see the joy and happiness dancing in his eyes.  when it does,  my heart jumps to the rhythm of his dancing eyes.  when his eyes are angry,  they are red from anger as if they were painted in red,  red blood.  you can see it only by his eyes.  his telling me something he cannot tell himself.  these eyes which are a lot like mine.     my mom and i have very different eyes.  her brown eyes,  the color of pure honey,  are like sea waves.  during high tide,  she enjoys childhood,  and is happy.  during low tide she is sad,  feels she missed something.  at low tide when her eyes are sad,  my eyes are sad as well.  if only eyes could talk between themselves.   \tmom says that when she first saw me,  she thought to herself,  what small eyes.    her sisters werenâ’t sure at the beginning i was my momâ’s.  they used to laugh about it.  my eyes seem to be peaceful,  she says.  she said: peaceful,  not happy.

title: Life of Sheep

title: I Hear Chinatown Singing
author: linda
text: i hear chinatown singing,  the varied carols i hear; those of chefs-each one singing his,  as it should be,  creative and precise; the waitress singing hers,  as she serve her customers or dishes,  the businessman singing his,  as he makes ready for work or leaves off work; the librarian singing what belongs to her in her library-the teacher singing on the school-ground; the poet singing as he sits on his chair-the musician singing hers as she plays guitar; the doctor's song-the nurse's,  on their way in the morning,  or at the noon intermission,  or at sundown; the lively singing of the children-or of the young wife,  at work-or of the husband counting or checking-each singing what belongs to him or her and to none else; the day what belongs to the day-at night,  the party of hard-working citizens,  happy,  proud; singing,  with open mouths,  their strong melodious songs.

title: I am

title: Poverty

text: along the dusty road, i trotted feeling empty and desolate some soft,  still voice kept reassuring me but my my heart was in pieces i felt a whirlwind on my head dreading to blow my brain into pieces i rounded a lonely corner that led to a desolate home standing on a hill like a ruined city slowly,  i approached  first i saw our kitchen the mud was peeling off the thatches were coming off everything stared at me as though appealing for help mother was seated on a log with a distant look on her eyes she didnt notice me approach i had to hide for a moment to weep away the tears then i approached her with a shuffle she saw me, i saw her she wiped a drop  and i smiled not a smile but an attempt to keep the tears away poverty,  poverty, where do you come from?

title: Machine

title: Conscience
author: lucy
text: he rolled around in a ditch of my conscience hitting the dirt,  the grass,  the images of my best friend and her flaming red hair he barrels over braces and bobby pins but not the drugs-  they cannot touch her here he rolls around with best friends of his own boys in dinosaur shirts,  camo shorts i wonder if the same story will be told watching the ditch,  he will stay the rest will drift with the wind,  away  itâ’s in my blood to lay down,  feign death i wonder if it courses through him,  too dad says,  â“son,  you can push back. â”  but i hope it is a gene he does not acquire the deep,  black anger; gentle suits him and i hope it is something in his veins,  not something the mind can change not something a father can arrange  he rolls around in a ditch of my conscience but it is not my conscience to claim others once played there people sang people danced there- itâ’s a collective conscience and heâ’s just rolling around in it his own conscience,  not yet decided

title: Treasure Hunt in the Closet
author: macey
text: a bright string,  and blacklight.  the string loops and loops around the track,  brightly illuminated by the light.  what remains from disney world,  however long it decomposes along with my old sweaters,  will always be new and shiny.   a bright shiny button,  created by yours truly.  a message of who i am and what i stand for.  able to display to whoever is wondering.   nothing is more comforting than dusty old relics being found when they never were truly lost in the first place.  old christmas presents from the museum gift shop gifts curled up in the nooks and crannies of my room.  dinosaur bones in the closet,  quite literally,  have been waiting to be dug up again.    shirts are like split personalities.  they all show someone new.  one second you are a football player sporting your jersey.  the next you are a choir performer singing on stage.  every now and then i like to become someone new while never actually changing who i am.

title: NatureÂ’s Invitation
author: macey
text: ever notice how everything moves in perfect harmony? a place for everything and everything in its place  everything outside seems to flow like music.  the bright greens and blues mix with the chirps of the birds,  barks of the dogs,  and the friendly chatter of my fellow park dwellers.   here mankind is one with nature.  the people donâ’t seem out  of their place here.   .  it is seldom you  find a place like this.  places where the grass welcomes us and we welcome it.  i welcome the grass  with open arms today  as i sit on this bench  writing about natureâ’s great hospitality.

title: Friendship Pyramid
author: macey
text: friendship is a bond that can never be broken.  it is a structure,  a pyramid,  that can only get stronger as it grows taller.  it may sometimes falter and buckle under its weight,  but if built correctly it will not fall.  we have all been a part of a pyramid at one point.  whether you are at the bottom bearing the weight of the group,  or on top along for the ride and the great view,  everyone has a part to play.  a part in maintaining the structure upholding the pyramid that is friendship.

title: The Maiden
author: mackenzie
text: there once was a city by the sea where a monster attacked.  quite horrid was he,  with breath of ice,  and eyes like battle spears.  he caused warriors to tremble and run.  run from that fiend,  flying far on the land then back out to sea.  this terrible evil,  this dragon of hate,  he tore down the city; torches set fire to the hills.  the flames flipped and flew,  spun beyond their control! no warrior came to save the city.  tâ’was not high on the hilltop,  but along next the gorge… no great man,  gallant and graceful.  no,  it was but a simple maid.  on the coast she had dwelt since the time of her birth.  the beast had made waste to her familyâ’s home; knocked down like building blocks,  causing no flower to bloom.  the girl was a pretty thing,  eyes sparkling jewels and hair of fine gold.  she needed no prod,  as some cattle or sheep in a pen,  to do her duty and daily services.  she floated like wafting smoke toward the fowl creature.  and when he looked upon her kaleidoscope eyes,  her teardrop face fresh from a fairytale.  the beast was enchanted by the figure of beauty.  even the mighty kingâ’s men,  equipped with broad shield and sword… advanced they were in weaponry,  and mounted on royal steeds.  this cavalry could not take the beast,  thus she did.  with the calm of her face,  and peace-speaking words,  the small girl did what mighty men could not.  for as soon as the eyes of the beast fell upon her,  he was drawn under her spell and turned to make his leave.  he rode on the waves,  back out to sea.  the girl returned to the cityâ’s great hall.  brave maiden she was,  and raised up on shoulders where the kingâ’s men shouted out to the wind,  chanting â“hurrah! hurrah! for the girl has saved us! hurrah!â” she was crowned in glory,  and remembered by all.   time passed by and all was well.  for three whole decades,  the city thrived.  all civil justice satisfied.  meanwhile,  the dragon swam in heated hellish places,  below the surface he dwelt in pain and agony.  for the great monster had vowed to never return,  and spoil the innocent with his jaws.  but he felt their blood upon his lips.  even thirty years later,  he felt the pull of that city,  that coastal banquet where the meat was so delicious.  so the dragon he made his way back to that place,  smashing apart isles along his way.  when he finally reached the borderline wall,  he knocked it down with a swish of his tail.  alarm bells went blaring,  the kingâ’s men attacked.  these were a fresh batch,  they had not learned their lesson when last he had come.  the beast could not be defeated by force,  but enchanted by love.  the king was wise,  and he remembered this fact,  he sent for the maiden who had saved them from their demise.  but when she came upon the beast,  her charm and her valor,  her strength was lost.  she was no longer young,  and pure and simple.  her golden hair had greyed,  and her eyes had dimmed when her shoulders drooped.  the dragon was no longer smitten by her beauty,  because that weapon had marred with age.  just when the city could have no hope,  their flags dropped down,  their weapons in pieces… another young maiden made her way among the crowd.  a girl with glittering eyes and hair of silk; these gifts endowed unto the child by mother eve herself.  she was the other maidenâ’s daughter,  and she declared before the king,  â“i will kill this beast once and for all! if thou will allow it,  for i certainly can. â” the king gave her favor,  and his very own dagger.  she went away,  to slay the best.   the dragon was a curse to all men.  he was out crushing houses with his feet,  gorging himself with gaunt,  waning bodies.  the girl came upon him with intelligence and grace,  and told him to halt in his tracks.  and when he looked upon her innocence,  still ripe and unmarred by age,  he was transfixed.  she spoke pleasing words unto him,  and he drew near,  close,  so that he was lulled to sleep in her lap.  the civilians exhausted from labor so hard,  they dared not cheer,  as to not wake the beast.  the maid stroked his head once,  then took hold the dagger.  she stabbed it right through an eye,  which was closed.  the blade sunk deep and true,  and it went back and killed him.  the city was free! the young girl had saved them.  she was chanted and cheered,  and raised up on shoulders by the kingâ’s men.  she was honored forever as the girl who had bested the beast.     rational: this piece is an imitation of the epic beowulf,  which was originally written and passed down as an oral tale in england between 8th and 11th centuries.

title: My Sidewalk Life
author: maddy
text: my sidewalk life  â“there is a place where the sidewalk ends. â” and life ends with it.   my life started with the cement being paved.  a new addition to the world.    over time the sidewalk hardenâ’s.   it develops stories and marks of its own.  it develops individuality the sidewalk endures storms and tragedies  for the people that walk over the sidewalk leave their impressions.   they leave stories in which only the sidewalk can tell.  the sidewalk watches as people pass it by,  it watches as time goes faster and faster.   but at some point there is a place where the sidewalk ends.    new additions are added,  with newer cement paved; added to the original.  the new cement makes the old stronger but it canâ’t seal the gap that continues to grow as the old sidewalk grows older.   grass grows in cracks now very distinct in the sidewalk it thrives for a time but eventually like everything  it grows into something nobody wants anymore and when the grass grows into weeds the weeds are sprayed away.   allowing the cracks to grow.    the sidewalk begins to whither away like everything in life.   and eventually it is reduced to sand and the sidewalk is forced to come to an end.   and life ends with it.

title: Five Senses of Freedom

text: i see the visions of past ,   visions that lived in the sight of citizenry,  it was to live and make the freedom last,  and make india repeat its history .   i taste those free thoughts roaming in search of rights ,  amidst the bloody riots  and those cruel fights.   now i smell the fragrance of peace ,  for dominance has lost its control.  and also did the imperialism cease when action was replaced with thought and soul.   i feel that sense of happiness and relief ,  that spread like a smile,  gone have the miseries and grief as the country chooses high profile.   finally i hear the freedom's voice,  that echoes all over the place the country has finally listened to it's people's choice as triumph and celebration apace.

title: An Unheard Plea

text: to you i'm the one that isnt the same but the rejection from you hisses when i say your name.  my plea for help isn't heard.  so your help isn't an option.  to see you standing there staring at me makes me want to run,  to show you my plea.  but if you were to come and find me there,  would you undersand,  would you stare,  or would talk with you friends as if i wasn't there? i try to cry out but all you hear is silence.  you wish i would leave and never had been.  but what you don't know is i feel alone and am starting to believe you.  my feelings of agony just pull me apart.  but i can't ask you for help for i fear rejection.  the pain grows worse with each day.  someday i hope you may come and ask me if i'm okay.

title: The Skateboarding Parasite
author: matt
text: â“the skateboarding parasiteâ”  i am a twisted ankle,  a broken bone,  and i always wear a helmet.   while a hospital visit is needed almost monthly,  but not enough time to pay the bill,  all thatâ’s needed is a bag of peas,  icey-hot,  and band-aids.    i am a sprained wrist and jammed toe,  bloody knuckles and a concussion.  built from tendonitis and strained ligaments,  a cracked rib and swollen elbows.   an insinuating sensation of pain,   is a constant parasite,  living in our minds,  feeding off all of us.   my best foot forward expels a dragon,  a beautiful,  flipping,  spinning monster,   sometimes i accidentally let it bite back.   the best thing i can do is learn from it.  and always wear a helmet.

title: Life
author: meg
text: life is a roller coaster it always has its ups,  downs,  and arounds sometimes it's a comedy like ''i love lucy'' at other times you are so sad it's a thunderstorm  it can be a romance novel you are deeply engrossed in or it may be a hurricane of hatred due to anger however,  each of us is a biological clock ticking our own lives away and we must live each day to its fullest  like jesus put himself last we must put others before us as a poor man who has nothing,  but gives everything he has we too,  must give rather than receive  we can be free like birds if,  instead of worrying,  we are peaceful and content as a feather floating in the wind,  we go in whatever direction we are taken and deal with the cards we are dealt,  whatever they may be  like a rose waiting to bloom,  humans must be patient things will not always go as we expect life is not always fair,  and some people are luckier than others however,  we must always be thankful  honesty is an essential trait to have we should always be kind and generous and try not to cause anyone pain as small as a broken heart but most of all,  life is a garden,  and we can't forget to stop and smell the roses.

title: Nature's Beauty
author: meg
text: natureâ’s beauty  as i sit down and listen to the world around me,  my thoughts come at me fast.  i take a deep breath and close my eyes wanting for nature to lure me in and open my mind to the cool silence all around me.  slowly,  i relax and my thoughts disappear.  the quiet voice of the wind beckons me as the soft touch of the grass lulls my tired mind.  birds nearby seem to sense my relaxed self as they gently sing their song.  as my eyes stay shut,  they seem to see for the first time all of the quiet that this world has to offer.  my senses comes alive and smell both the dirt beneath my feet and the flowers nearby.  hushed sounds fill my ears and my soul.  my eyes open to the sounds of feet walking past.  do they know of the wonders of these woods? have others slowed down their pace and let the trees speak to them? how long have i ignored the silence within me nature seems to provide? so naturally and uncomplicated the silence will linger within me  long after today and my days to come.  no more will i let the rush of my days go by without retuning to this spot,  these woods,  and remembering the way they asked me to join them inside  into their secret world that i am now a part of.    \u000c

title: Life?
author: megan
text: i have seen it happen.  i have read stories about it.  it seems to be everywhere i am and in whatever i read.  i run and run but it just keeps chasing after me.   i call for help,    i even scream.  it wont leave,  it wont leave!   i want to stop and let it take me away,  but i know there's a reason why i'm not stopping.   maybe it's someone i will meet along the way that is also running.  maybe it's the places i will see.  or maybe just what will happen in the future.   it's a mystery.  lets not stop and we will see.

title: Charleston
author: mikayla
text: i walk along the cracked pavement,  its repair is way past due.   what once was beautiful and new now being trampled under the feet of pedestrians, j-walkers,  charlestonians?  no,  they couldnt be.   for they stomp on this elegant cracked pavement in a daze.  they pay no attention to the history around them.  they don't love the city like i do.   i can see the spirits oozing from the walls of the aged buildings.  i hear the tread of the horses hoofs still clacking along the cobblestone.   i feel the past push through me.  the presence of women in elegant dresses and important men in white powdered wigs.  i hear the guns crack,  the cannons fire,  and the widdows cry.  i see the peace after the war.  the celebration,  the relief.   i watch hundreds of years of history pass before my eyes.  and i pause to take in the wonder of the old elegent city i live in.  but i must keep on going,  so as not to be trampled like the beautiful,  old,  cracked,  pavement.

text: iâ’m dreaming of a star,  wondering what you are.  i see you all the time,  but my words fail,  and i try to mime.  arms flapping like a seal begging for his meal,  and my heart sinks,  my life stinks,  why oh why canâ’t one think?  iâ’m dreaming of a star,  and admiring from afar.  watching closely,  hanging on ever move you make.  donâ’t take,  me as a stalker,  iâ’m simply so in love,  words are above all emotion.  my tongue goes limp when your near,  my eyes go blurry,  and my ears canâ’t hear.  is this love or motion sickness?  iâ’m dreaming of a star,  hoping it wonâ’t leave a scar.  for my heart can speak,  if only you heart would listen.  a picture may be worth a thousand words,  and a smile a million miles,  but just the sight of you eyes is worth a library,  and a trip to the sun.

title: The Castle

title: A Figure in the Night

text: the bright pale moon shines down upon the land,  its light illuminates the world below; beneath the trees a figure stands so grand,   his hard,  black hooves dug firmly in the snow; strong antlers rising proudly on his head,   his fur lay smooth and sleek upon his skin,  the snowy white ground on which he treads,  its bright,  white glow,  as if lit from within; with pride he lifts his head up to the sky,  and bellows,  letting out his mournful song,  for on his chest,  a bloody wound lies,  his feet collapse,  he is no longer strong; his eyes close shut,  his spirit lifts in flight,  the stagâ’s brave soul,  now free to run tonight.

title: Survivor
author: natalie
text: torn from her home at the age of ten a girl watches her mother's fear-stricken face,  so far away.  she lifts her hand and reaches out but touches only empty air.  she screams,  but the sound merely drifts away.   a shot,   and the light is swept from her mother's eyes,  life shattered like glass,  nothing left but glistening rubies that spread in a pool on the pavement.   silence.  the man's swastika glares at her,  sternly like the man's eyes that are lifeless and cold,  glazed over with lies and lament is gone but buried deep within.   shipped away to a place as horrible,  they say,   where fear and pain stamp out hope where hunger scratches with merciless claws and love falls away with the tears that rain from weary eyes.   and drawn from her cracked and bleeding lips bursting from her withered,  pain-stretched soul a song takes flight,  sweet as red velvet,  a cry that pierces the gray skies so that god himself peers down from heaven,  the wretched cry breaking his mighty throne.   freed.  even then,  shame burdens as they walk the moonlit streets.  their sorrow weighing down their skeletal bodies,  so alone,  with no where to go.   eyes follow the tattered frames.  creatures,  they say,  horrid creatures.  but they don't know.  they don't know.   it was real.  it's not just a memory.  they lived it.  let them speak.

title: People.
author: nathan
text: people tell you your life is defined,  shaped and carved into a path that youâ’re born into.   unchangeable.  solid.    people tell you there are those who get lucky,   the ones that break through,   the ones that change the world for the followers.  those followers that work as the cogs in a machine we call,  â“the circle of lifeâ”  people have told me that i am who i am,  and to accept myself for who i am as a person.  to be the person that society needs or wants.  i want to be the person that i need in my life,  but people can be a disappointment.  even yourself is susceptible to that.    people have warned me not to stray too far from the beaten path.  the one that billions have walked upon before me.  they have warned me of the dangers of becoming an outcast from the rest.  the feeling of knowing that one wrong step,  leads to an abyss of darkness.  knowing that you canâ’t go back to the path that you have previously betrayed.        people will come and go.  on the path that they feel defines their unique and special personalities.  at a crossroads with the person you were meant to be,  and the person you are.  on another path that others have tread,   forging a new wave of thoughts,  ideas,  and philosophies.  mine being yet another branch in the ever growing tree of life.  their thoughts and beliefs wiped away like the rise of high tide.                                                             people will leave.

title: Summer Haze
author: nathan
text: summer friends; fun.  the entirety of late nights.  bike rides into oblivion.  days and nights with the â“squadâ” fighting curfew till the last instants.   three whole months gone in what was a day,  wishing it was eternity.  stories to tell,  secrets to keep,  and jokes that will make us laugh just as hard as the first time.  when the words good times enter your mind,   the word summer tags along with it.  school just drags you down.   loud music; louder thoughts.  long phone calls full of white noise,   just hoping that the person on the other end can bare you.  alas a lasting conversation,  can last a lifetime in my mind.   just me,  my friends and our time in the summer.  wishing it would never end.

title: Me
