title: Where I'm From
author: nora
text: i am from free documents from inked declaration and constitution.  i am from fenced backyards,  a small enough hole,   to break away,  if needed.  i am from a land of no doubt,  that holds the parchment up high,   ascending and breezing,   along with the wind.   i'm from hats and buckles,  from innate dialect spoken with effortless tunes,  gone with the wind.  i'm from a bottomless pit,  a well so deep,   with black-holes underneath,  yet air clung to the walls,   expanding and expanding.   i'm from cattle on a bun,  sprinkled with spices.  from the cement that traced the banal equator,  along number four.   i'm from the mind of determination,  from logic and intelligemce that poked opaque holes in my mind.  from the fastidious and abstruse rhythm that scarred the trees.   i am from tranquility,  melancholy,  and insecurity that plagued my thoughts.  i am from a galaxy of eight stars,   from gregarious and austere souls.  i am from autonomous flesh,  antithetic from the bones of my father,  yet drowned in extolled and benign blood is where i'm from.

title: The Art of Art
author: orion
text: i had a dream last night,  that i was in the middle of the sky,  god,  the sunrise was so beautiful,  i then woke up,  confined by four graying walls,  that enveloped my eyes in a world of grayer light,  footsteps,  footsteps,  on creaky floors of dusty wood,  a door hangs cracked,  a bulb unshaded,  coated in layers of dis-use,   the washroom,  kept tidy by meticulous effort,  is a closet bathed in golden beams of pure sun,  beams shoot across the pale sky from the east,  the water may be cold and the toothpaste looking rather low,  but none of that matters when the sky is made into swirls,  of the palest blues and the brightest golds,  which turn the clouds into flowerbeds and the sky into a symphony,   our van,  all dented and worn by years of service,  i use as a thinking cap for my thoughts to settle,  wondering,  wondering,  my head processing to the beat of the drum,  from the radio,  my ideas flow with songs which play,  like water running in a continuous circle,  running in laps around my head,  about news,  politics,  art,  peace,  war,  the delicacies of man,  the tools of the great play,  one i will to be known as part of,   there is nothing romantic about school,  a place in which we are taught the truth of conformity,  the great march of progress designed by rulers,  of nations falsely claimed as divided,  on one earth,  an earth which is suffocating under the weight of our wars,  wars against hatred,  pain,  loss,  each other,  we fight peril with peril which shows,  that we are not doomed,  there is still a chance,  schools will one day teach one world,  one people,  we will learn to share without leaders,  and to make decisions without war,  to love and to live without getting tired of it,   my grandmother once told me,  there is no food in heaven,  food is a pleasure of the mortal and has no use in heaven,  well,  in that case there is no need for dance in heaven,  no need of conversation,  of art,  we just sit,  as you have designed in your mind,  on clouds in white blouses,  playing harps for the rest of eternity,  then i canâ’t blame angels for coming down here,  and â“blessing usâ” with their magical gifts,  gifts that if i talked about them without angels youâ’d call witchcraft,  is food witchcraft? is dancing the art of the devil? do you see my five-pointed star drawn in a circle on the ground,  while i eat my cheese and crackers? no? then weâ’re good,  iâ’ll dine with you in heaven,   a voice is worth dying for,  for dying takes time,  the same amount of time,  i would spend listening to you talk,  voices which paint pictures that sing marvelous songs,  a garden is grown in an hour of talk,  with chrysanthemums and roses,  roses of all colors; red,  blue,  white,  and yellow,  gardens which blossom into orchards,  that grow apples of pure gold,  that are harvested by nightingales,  that fly from north to south and south to north,  over and over again until death do they part from this world,  so yes,  a voice is worth dying for  so is this world so sad? is life as grim as you make it out to be? can you not see past these wars which our fathers fight? can you not see why i laugh,  why i dance,  the world is not sad,  and i do not frown,  for i know what pain is,  i have known loss,  i am fluent in the language of hate,  but that doesnâ’t stop the sun from setting or rising,  nor does it stop the birds from singing,  so why should it stop you or me?

title: I miss you and the way things used to be
author: paige
text: i miss you and the way things used to be.   we used to open up and talk forever,  i listened to you and you listened to me.  we hugged and kissed; it was so care free.   you always managed to make feel like everything would be all right,  even on my worst days you could make my smile bright.   our friendship had an extra spark,  whenever we were together we lit up the dark.  but the two of us could not see what everyone else could see,  that there was love between you and me.   we stayed just friends as long as we could,  that made things easy and easy was good.  but that all changed when one day i found that my blindness for you was gone.  i could then see what everyone else could see,  that there was love between you and me.   i went off to tell you i feel,  without second-guessing that how i felt was real.  but when i did,  i realized i was too late.  your blindness still existed; it had not been set free.  instead you gained sight for a girl who unfortunately wasn't me.    i look back at all the time that you watched me want every other guy.  you told me it didn't bother you,  was that the truth or just a lie? i sit here today and watch you do what i had done,  nothing hurts more,  the pain is no fun.   remaining just friends is an option,  you think we should.  but it would no longer be easy,  no longer be good.    it's sad to say but this time you can't make me feel like everything will be all right.  because of you my smile has died,  it is no longer bright.   we no longer call each other a friend,  because the relationship we had has come to an end.  so now we both part,  and even though you hurt me so much,  you will remain in my heart.  you probably can't say the same for me,  you have moved on just fine,  and maybe someday so will i.  it will be hard,  but i will try.  to you i may have been just another girl,  but to me you were not just another guy.    and i will still hope for the day to come when you gain sight,  and realize that me and you is whatâ’s right.   or maybe it's just way too late.  maybe after all it was never fate.  so now i must move on with the future and set our past free.  i'll stop missing you and the way things use to be.

title: Something that Mattered

title: Fake faces
author: prerna
text: i live among faces,  where i search for a real face.  you'll never find a real face,  no matter whosoever you gaze.   every face has an untold story,  revealing the past experiences and glory.  a sound of the heart never raised ; finding way in its own maze.   true faces of childhood are driven away,  like petals of flowers falling away.  a child is a sweet sensation,  vulnerable to millions of exploitation.   the sweet smile is taken from the early age,  and the voice becomes a bird in the cage.  the gems of happiness are invisible,  behind the fake faces of fables.   happiness is to lose yourself in,  far from the world of sin.  happiness is not a race.  it is appropriate for a face.

title: A fault by me

text: a fault by me has made all the difference.  i was a happy person a day before.  today,  for friends i roar.   i prayed to all the gods,  to make my life without foes.  earlier,  i had many friends.  now,  every friend from my life goes.   everyone relies on human connections.  love,  care and affection.  i became a tree without fruits.  since,  i was separated from my roots.   my nights became sleepless.  my thoughts became endless.  everyday became a new fight.  for me,  being quite was right.   my boat is sailing all alone,  in an endless deep ocean.  for long my boat wouldn't last,  since the world is too fast.

title: I May Not.
author: reshu
text: i may not want you,  but i need you.  i may not have faith in you,  but i believe you.  i may not show care for you,  but i really do.  i may not call you my success,  but you are my strength.  i may not feel what i want,  but my feelings are just for you.  i may not call you,  but my soul always talks to you.  i may not be visible to you,  but i always see you.  i may not show love for you,  but i really do.  i may not be wrong,  but want to prove myself totally right.  i may not recover your past,  but want to create your future.   i may not know this sensation but i really do,  the thing i want to say is really true,  there is something for you,  i love you.

title: The truth about friendship

text: when we hang out it's like as if i have no       worries.    when we drive in my car we have fun.   when we go shopping or on a cruise we pretend.   sometimes i don't even want to go  home.   your my true friend and its great to have a friend that cares so much.   i'll be there for you like you've been there for me.   it's the best when we hang out and act goofy.    so i want to say thanks for being my friend.

title: Autobiographical
author: ryan
text: two roads diverged in a yellow wood,  as many decide to take the one many others venture on.  it may be successful,   it may not,  but how can one be successful,  when being confined like a herd,  without exit.  i choose the one harder to envision for most,   undesirable,   maybe,   maybe not,   success comes to the person who makes the hard right,  not the easy wrong.  so as i go on this enormous,   miraculous,  journey,  they call life,  i will strive for the road less traveled by,  and hopefully,  that will make all the difference.

title: My Haikus
author: ryan
text: paper's seduction and my pencil's ideas stolen ideas.   within these pages endless possibilities may it contain songs. . .   a flash of beauty-- though short and simple it lasts an eternity  life in a small cage claustrophobic and pensive-- stare without seeing.   provocative words-- explicit and musical letters learn to dance!  five fingers on a hand on a dangerous arm,  linked in loving prose. . .   should the heart make music . . . in the presence of the mind would the mind listen. . .   mother and father caught in a loving embrace-- they won't fool anyone!

title: I Am From
author: samantha
text: i am from worn out cleats and smelly shinguards from bathtubs and raggedy washcloths.  i am from the pile of clean socks in a basket in the corner smelling like fresh laundry.  i am from the oak tree.  from the burning bush, whose fiery red limbs show the seasons true colors creeping up behind us.  i am from christmas and growing up tall.   from shirley,  whose farm town past makes for detailed stories told around the dinner table.   words spoken,  but not heard.   i am from talking too loud and eating too fast.  from sleeping in too late.    i am from mind your manners and bed before 10,  from come inside dinner is ready,   wash your hands.  i am from that one space where the basketballs get swallowed into the darkness underneath the back deck,  from infinite hours and fantasies taking place in my very own backyard.  i went to egypt.  and france.  i rode a ship across the ocean.  i was a superhero.   dreams ruined by â“come inside dinner is ready. â”   i am from i love you moreâ’s and it was him not meâ’s.   i am from family.  we are from picking pumpkins in an unknown city,  from chicken and casseroles.   we are from packing away our life for the place who turn children into adults,  bright eyed,  ready to explore,  leaving loved ones behind.  from vacations unforgettable.   we are from old dust covered photo albums piled on the shelves in our basement,  snippets from our childhood.   my brothers,  my mom,  my dad.   the tables have turned though,  all has left.   itâ’s me,  the only child left in this house.

title: Standing
author: samantha
text: some days i am lustrous colors,  full of energy,  full of pride standing tall with others.  other days i am dull grey colors bare and alone,  picked of my petals petals of pride falling,  slowly,  one by one standing there,  melancholy,  with no one around to help build my petals back

title: ''That September Day''
author: sarah
text: no one will ever forget what happened on that day; september eleventh touched many people in a very special way.   we couldn't fight the battle we had no time to try; many people just burst out and then started to cry.   some lost a loved one which would make anyone sad; others just held on thanking god for what they had.   many fire fighters came  some stayed at their stations; we saw how we could work together under one now united nation.   we came together  like never before; and pushed those terrorists right out the door.   they tried to pull our nation apart they didn't pass,  but fail; so when we capture all of them they won't get out on bail.   as we can see  our nations now strong; we stick together  when things seem to go wrong.   so we'll nevetr forget although the day is done; we'll never forget september eleventh two-thousand and one.

title: Some things
author: sarah
text: somethings are meant to be,  some things are not,  either way you look at it though,   you know you can' t go wrong.   pick a direction,   any direction you like,  whatever you choose,  i'm sure you won't think twice.   make choices,  make mistakes,  that's what life is all about,  but no matter what,  you can do anything,  determination is all it takes.   some things are worth the trouble,  some things are not,  some juice is worth the squeeze,  some is nothing but a problem.   no matter how you look at it,  no matter what happens,  some things are meant to be,  some things,  you just can't pick. . .

title: HEALING WOUNDS
author: sarah
text: why does it have to be like this? there are so many opportunities that i miss.  i want to be with you.  i want to talk with you like we used to.  those were the great ole days.   you were always in a daze,  thinking of everyone but yourself.  even when you would hurt yourself.  it was never about you.  it was always about the people around you.  i could tell you anything and everything.  you would not hold any of it against me for anything! then we got into a fight.  now i realize that you were right.  things happen for a reason.  i guess we were the type of friends that only last for a season.  some things,  however,  will never part.  you will always hold a special place in my heart.  you are a really great guy,  that is one thing i definitely cannot deny.  i will always be here for you.  i am always open for you to tell your little stories to.  i know that it has not been too evident lately,  but i really do care for you greatly.  i will always love you no matter what.  god put you in my life for a purpose we cannot see yet but,  i know he will reveal it sooner or later.  i just hope its sooner than later.  my biggest fear is that it will be too late,  to show you how much i love you,  despite all the hate.  we have tried and tried to be great friends.  at first it looks as if we are doing fairly well,  then that one ends.  i hope and pray that as time goes on,  we will be able to carry on with the friendship that we once had,  without turning it into something bad.  you know i will always love you,  and i know the same is true when it comes to you.  sometimes when i just really feel like giving up on this whole thing,  i think of that very something that you used to always tell me.  dont ever give up!  listen to me! i dont know what i would do if you never would have come into my life.  its people like you that leave an impression on someones life.  dont ever give up and stay strong in the lord.  he paid your debt that you could not afford.  always remember this very thing,  and never forget that you are everything that someone out there is looking for.  you may get anxious as the days become more and more.  just dont rush into things you dont want to do.  always remember: god is watching everything you do!

title: WHY
author: sarah
text: why do i act as if everythings great? why do i cause so much hate? why is it so hard to tell my parents,  i love you? why do i see bad in all that i do? why is it that i cant show people how much i care? why is it that when people see me they stop and stare? why is it that no matter what i do i end up doing wrong? why is it that i try to cover my hurt with song? why do i not tell people what i really feel? why dont i let people in on the deal? why do i act the way i do? why is it that no matter what the circumstance,  someone is always there to say,  its all right,  i love you? why is it that im so lucky to have people here for me no matter what? why is it that gods blessed me no matter what? why is it that god chose me to be a witness for others? why is it that we sometimes cant stand our fathers and tend to drift towards our mothers? why is it that no matter how hard i try,  i just cant deal with the fact that i dont always know what to do? why is it that i tell angela and sean i cant stand you instead of i love you? why is it that i sometimes feel intimidated by the people that care for me the most? why is it that i dont like when people boast? why is it that i cant let charity,  daniel,  or stuart know how much i love them? why is it that i think im fat and i wish i was slim? why is it that god works differently in everybodys lives? why is it that when i do some of the stupidest things,  it feels as if ive been stabbed in the back with a thousand knives? why is it that i got so lucky as to have such a beautiful little girl in my family? why is it that im still anxious when im around certain people,  especially if theyre in my family? why is it that im so lucky to have such a great brother in law like daniel when i couldve been stuck with someone like israel adam carter? why is it that i settle for the least i can do (whether with school or in my relationship with god) when i know i should try harder? why is it that i question all these things? why dont i just trust that god loves me and will continue to bless me with great things? why is it that i ask all these questions when i know only god knows the answers to most of them? why can't i just stop all this and give it all to him?

title: Heaven Bound
author: sarah
text: i look at him and all i can see is all the love he's given me.  he was always willing to lend a hand,  and always wanted to be a good friend.   but now he's gone to heaven,  his sins were all,  by god,  forgiven.  through his life and through his death,  many have stopped to think of their own deaths.  where will i go when i die? he knew he was bound for heaven,  and that's no lie.  now i ask you,  where will you live eternally? hopefully in heaven with him and me.

text: moses had died and israel did need a leader,  of which joshua did succeed god spoke to him and gave him commands that im sure shook joshuaâ’s very hands you will lead israel,  god told him then but you must think right before you begin strength and courage is what you need  and obedience to the law,  then you will succeed i made a promise i must fulfill if only you will do my will the law that moses gave to you you must be so careful to do everything i have written in it if you ponder its many commands i will take you in my hands and canaan will surely get hit joshua,  are you listening to me? you must stand firm with bravery do not be fearful or overwhelmed those qualities get you nowhere,  i have found and donâ’t forget if you obey i will be with you all the way.

title: Smells from Underneath

title: Small Things
author: savannah
text: those eyes are such a beautiful shade of green.  forest green.  and i'm not talking about the regular old green you see from the outskirts.  i'm talking about the deep green that you see when you're standing in the very middle of the forest,  so far away from the outside that you could swear you were the only human alive.   the way those pink lips wrap around the cigarette that you hold so delicately in your hand.  the hand that's scattered with black ink and deep meanings.  they're such a beautiful shade of pink.  i'm not talking about the pstel shade of pink that you see in the spring.  i'm talking about the shade of oink that my cheeks turn whenever you call me

title: Me
author: schanay
text: i have green eyes,  and blond hair.  my skin is pale,  and my hands are cold.  i have clown feet,  and amazon legs.  i'm very,  very unique.

title: The Nose
author: scott
text: it's my most noticable feature.  it's big,  crooked,  and uniquely me.   my voice comes through my nose,  and sometimes,  from the side,  i look like i have a beak.   but i love my nose.  no one has one like it,   but me.

title: Collision
author: scyla
text: the air hangs heavy,  a thick quilt donned atop the scape.  dark red tension drifts through the atmosphere,  mingling with the scent of forget-me-nots and wild roses.  a fall storm gathers in the north,  intensifying the orange of the fiery sunset.  the light reflected off the pool in the olive grove withers.   while humid,  foreboding winds ripple across the surface.    crack!  the first bolt strikes the ground,  rattling the earth at its base.  an arpeggio of lightning follows,  with broken chords of rolling thunder.  hail crashes down accompanied by a monsoon.  squeezing through the rain,  long,  malicious claws descend from the heavens,  strewing the soil haphazardly.  wind usurps the bodyâ’s reign over the lungs,  a black hole vacuuming the universe into an empty abyss.  the earth wails in agony,   its skin lacerated by harsh discords of destruction,  a horrid cacophony of desolated spirits.  two opposing forces collide without consideration of repercussions,  as ears thunder with the terrible symphony that rebounds off every wall.  its ballad lasts seemingly forever,  but the trumpeting counter melody reaches its decrescendo.  the shouting storm silences,   dissipating across the horizon forever.  what remains is the crumbling pieces of a once whole life,  and an aqua light emanating from the pool,  refracting the rays of a golden dawn.  the last asylum for a weary heart.

title: Rainy Day
author: shannon
text: let the first drops of rain sound as the rest fall from the grey sky.  let them fall quickly to the ground for the cool water will soon dry and the child will not have long in the puddle to play.  let the drops fall where they belong in the little boyâ’s day.  let them linger on his little lips and revive his happy squeals.  let the heavy tears drip as he dreams of the surreal.  let the and grass grow and his throat cool and let it stay so his face can glow before the african sun takes it away.

title: A Fond Farwell
author: shannon
text: in our hearts,  you'll always stay.  in our minds,   we'll hear your voice.  in our prayers,  our hope will remain.  that one day,  one day,  when we're gone.  when our turn comes.   you'll be the one,  to see us through.  to show us the way.  to help us reach,  the golden gates.   so,  in our hearts,  you'll always stay.  as in our mind,  and prayers we'll always say.  we love you,  we miss you.  and we wish you,  a fond farewell.

title: The Minds Power
author: shannon
text: the power of the mind is a tricky thing.  you have to know just what you want.  you can't let it run  wild,  or free.   at least,  not without the imagination's release.    for if you should let it run away with you,  then the power could become to great.   it could take you to unknown worlds,  and places.  it could take you and change you form into new,  and exicted ways.   you could become a cat or a dophine.  you could even appear on other worlds.   life it's self will change for ever more.  and who's to say this is a bad thing?  for you might meet the other travlers.  and learn what they've learned.   then return to the world of control,    and worry.    where the imagination will,  is caged up.  at least,  till the next time,  you let it run away,  with you.  for that is the minds power.

you're the best thing that i ever knew i promise to always be here because life wouldn't be the same without you there is something important three words i need to say they are ''i love you'' and that feeling will never go away sorry for anything that i have made wrong i'll try my best to make it right because i couldn't bear one day without you or one dream at night. i think of you all the time you are something i've never had and you make me feel real alive when i am with you, i could never be sad you are what wakes me up in the morning you are why i go to sleep it's the things that you say that makes everything o. k. you probably have no idea that your touch makes my heart pick up its pace and i love everything about you even the way that you gaze down at my face! you know that i can't wait to see you and there is one thing i especially miss

title: The feel to be free..
author: simran
text: i don't care how many circumstances hurdle up for like a shining star i'll always shine and call out, ''whats up?''  many walls will stand between me and my 'happiness',  i know; but we won't worry because we can do it by ourselves,  we won't go with the flow. .   probably in the future my story won't get an applause,  but then everyone shall know that what is happening, is happening with a cause. .  i know that in the present i am to be hurt; but isn't that what life is-sometimes sorrow, sometimes mirth!?. .   no matter what happens and how,  i'll always be there,  i'll always share and forever care.   it all seems to be present,  it all seems to be true; all those fairy tales, they come alive but only with you. .   but do you know who is this 'you',  whom i do refer to?. .  it's myself, it is me enjoying the feel to be free!!!

title: Unbroken
author: sirina
text: she hides a ravine in her eyes,  her broken dreams compelled her to,  but there's a certain cyclone i see in them,  and tears like a tycoon,   why is everything so dark in here? everyone else is alive,  but she's lifeless,  this chelsea smile etched on her lips,  everything hides behind them,  the faith she used to put in you has slashed down like rubble,  now all she relies upon is a canid,  her soul is too subtle,  she could give a glut of her emotions to them,  but the greedy need fire,  heart so nevious,  it's frozen so cold like a dead desire,  i could clutch her in my arms,  caress her lips,  observe her hair,  but nothing can fix,  she's shattered deep down,  and is vulnerable to all my tricks her tattered memories ask me to walk away,  like she hates me! i can see right through her walls she has built with fear and screams,  but even her breath is mesmerising,  although she won't get it,  she could slice her flawless skin just to escape from the fit. .  but i really love you,  trapped inside this mirror i can do nothing,  my flesh has rusted to the bones but i am still living,  existing,  but not alive,  colourful,  but lifeless,  the ironies can't be defined,  they snatched away all her pieces,  but yet she's still alive in this lie,  her lips would tell a thousand truths,  lies,  all unspoken but she's breathing today,  alive,  unbroken. .

title: Hidden Park
author: sofiya
text: the sun starts to set,  pink and purple mixes with blue.  there sits a park,   secluded from the world.  if you swing high enough,  you can see cars race up and down woodward.  the yellow plastic slide looms in the shadow of the bushes.  you can see ''footprints''  left behind by strangers.   carvings of ''sally was here''  and dates from the '80s.  if youre small enough,   you can slide down  and see more footprints left behind.  i slip down  and land on the mushy woodchips.  i look up to see darkness.  leaving,  i take one last look,  before facing the streetlamps.

title: I Believe
author: sonia
text: the past has gone once again and the present has taken its place.  living in a world of deception is one of the hardest effects to face.   traveling from one location to another can make life so desperate.  what is the point of all this,  when we just get an increased view called the hypocrite?   but a new destination and goals arrive just by dragging the head.     disposing pieces of energy all in the respect of going from blue to red.   already being a red but living in a blue can make the mind feel illegal.  everyday experiencing nothing but lower cast and discrimination of not being an equal.                                                                                                                                                               it isn't the easiest thing,  but how can we resist it when there is no other choice.  this was the place where,  only the first voice of life could be heard,  and to carry on life always feeling so moist.   being uncontrollable of how ones' fait can be destined can sometimes be such a tragedy.  because no matter how much the positive side one hangs on to,  everything stays the same in reality.   but now a red going to unite with the other reds,  can make matters even worse instead of being delighted.  although transferring to an area of the same type,  can create no more than an empty mind constantly trying to be highlighted.   not knowing the language,  tradition,  culture and environment makes one imitate those who stand still and do nothing more.  for what could one do when all their moments were only acknowledged by the blues in a whole new world with different rules of sore.   being locked up in a cage once more because the judgment of the reds can be so disappointing.  finally after years of coming back all to be received are just critical responses only being discouraging.   the more harder we try,  the more the reds mock.  because as they say we do not speak the mother's tongue and insult us until we wish to become a hawk.   to the red's what only matters is whether who's better or not.  the fact never changes,  it's back to the start where one feels put out of place and exists only like a dot.   once again,  when in doubt if life will be over soon,  and want to talk,  cry and scream,  it is impossible.  all is needed is a sister,  but where is she,  nowhere to be seen because there is no history which makes everything unjustifiable.   when turned to the person who's role is to care about the children,  only does nothing but make you wish you were never left alone with her.  and then there's the older male who is suppose to act and talk more intelligent but obviously there's nothing more to achieve from him than a cats per.    the other male who's fully grown and couldn't take the crazy world he was brought in,  thought the only solution was to strive on his own and who knows what outrageous things are on his mind,  maybe he's walking on some cane.  though the head of the family is the only one who shows he cares proved he is the only one sane.   now that the reds have finally returned to their kingdom,  they are only greeted with cruelty.  from the maternal's side,  they are only here to take advantage and wreck the moments of loyalty.   while the same goes from the paternal side,  all that can be seen is betrayal and dishonour.  so you can see that i am really lost in a world of deception and depression trying to earn some honour.   but no matter what,  i still survived,  even through the toughest situations,  i kept my head up high.  after autumn when the leaves fall,  comes spring when the blossoms bloom and the weeds die.   because what a family does and says isn't what really counts,  but what does is the love they give and the smiles they put across a face to make happiness with the heart.  instead of being miserable,  i've learned to be thankful of so much more,  like the house i have and the friend who acts like a real sister,  for she is the one who creates the art.   all around,  all i could ever see were the painful experiences,  but i learned to conquer them all.   because life is just a game and to win all we have to do is know all the rules and achive the goal.   i believe one day,  i will be accepted as an equal and be respected like another as long as i pray to god and cope.  it doesn't matter where ever you are,  life can always change if you will,  for there's always hope. . .

title: The Rescuers
author: spencer
text: sometimes,  we walk in this pain,  and we need someone to rescue from our pain but from what? really. . .  from what?  that is the point what do we really need rescuing from? the pain we live? or the sorrow that we want to escape?  but realize this each time we endure pain and sorrow,  it makes us stronger so we must be strong we cannot let the pain and sorrow take over us and make us do crazy stuff instead we must be the one to win over the pain and sorrow to become the new of us the change the friendship the family the love the way we are the way we live  and one day we shall find each other and one day we shall care for each other and one day we shall share our pain and sorrow together this is the rescue we all need the answer is everyone sharing their love together let the love in,  and let it beat the pain and sorrow and be there for each others. . .   in life,  i ask a question will i be there for you? and my answer is,  i promise you,  i will be there for people who really need someone to come to their rescue and i will try my best to reach you  even though,  i might not be a very really good talker even though,  i might not be a good listener even though,  i might not be the person who can make you smile most,  but i know this,  i will always be there for you if you need someone,  a shoulder to cry on i shall be the one  and i have a question for all of you,  will you be the rescuer?

author: stephanie
text: memories are heartbeats sounding through the years echoes never fading of our smiles and our tears.  moments that are captured sometimes unaware pictured in an album or a lock of hair.  images that linger deep within the mind bit of verse we cherished once upon a time.  through the musty hallways of the days we knew ever comes the vision beautiful and true.  memories are roses blooming evermore full of fragrant sweetness never known before.  life must have a meaning goals for which to strive memories are lights that burn to keep the heart alive.

title: Memory
author: stephanie
text: in school they hammer it into your head; two plus two always equals four,  saturn is number six out of nine,   massachusetts' state flower is ironically the mayflower,  and the capital of paraguay is in fact asuncion.   bud do these random facts really matter? aside from high sat scores,  which will lead to good cholleges,  and in turn a well-paid job,   will you really need to know what the capital of columbia is? (bogata by the way)  when you're a forty-year-old ceo of some big corporation,   slacing away to make even more money to buy things you don't need,   you won't care that the square root of 169 is thirteen.   when you're forty years old,   it won't matter that you don't remember that john steinbeck wrote the grapes of wrath,  or that it was hannibal who used the elephants to cross the alps.   while you're sitting at that desk,  mindlessly typing emails about your company's future,   you'll recall the important stuff,  memories about wandering the streets with the best friends you once,  and hopefully  still have.   you won't even care that it was christopher columbus who  sailed teh ocean blue in 1492,  because you'll be too busy recalling that it was  exactly 2pm on june 17th when you and your friends decided just to just get in your car and drive eight hours to pennsylvania to  have a genuine philly steak and cheese.   so even if you forget that a2 + b2 = c2,  who cares? because the important things will be with you forever.

title: The Mourning
author: susan
text: twas a dark night i was left alone and from outside i heard a moan a moan so deep and sorrowful it made my tears well up and flow  i begin to nod off but later awake to a sound so mournful i just cannot take the horrible cries of anger and grief i will help the creature to find some relief  i venture outdoors where darkness prevails to the spot where the noise is i must stop the wails huddled in a corner underneath the brush the little animal spots me and comes to a hush  i crouch down to my knees and proceed on my quest it retreats to the space and hides at its best i peek under the steps i cannot find it there i finally decide it returned to its lair  many years ago this happened but i still wonder â‘bout it so where,  i ponder did that creature go is it still living? what if itâ’s dead? is it laughing cheerily? or is it woeful and sad?  i guess i will never know the horrors that the animal  had to face that caused the pain  and made it cry so doleful all my days i will remember  it ringing through my ears it will haunt me through my life and follow me all my years.

title: Good Morning
author: suzie
text: good morning   night falls, the sky is gloomy,  and day vanishes without a trace   gentle breeze brushes the tears off my face   grieved that time bent   bless the divine being that another day is waiting to descend    crying to my shadow,  asking it if i can bare the pain of waiting.

title: Animal in me
author: syafizee
text: the animal in me is confused,  the human in me is amused,   is it legal for me to call myself an animal? whilst human what i try to be.   when fishes flew and forests walked,  and figs grew upon thorn,  some moment when the moon was blood,  then surely i was born.   as a woman i have my season,  when you can capture me on heat,  till today,  i do not understand the reason,  why i hunt then,  like an animal hunting for its meat.   sometimes i show bravery like a lion,  with nerves of steel made of iron,  sometimes i give off a scent,  in the heat of the moment.  with monstrous head and sickening cry,  and ears like errant wings,  the devilâ’s walking parody,  on all four-footed things.   the tattered outlaw of the earth,  of ancient crooked will,  starve,  scourge,  deride me i am dumb,  i keep my secret still.   fools,  for i also had my hour,  one far fierce hour and sweet,  there was a shout about my ears and palms before my feet.   the animal in me is confused,  the human in me is amused  is it legal for me to call myself an animal? without being a cannibal.

text: i never thought that a time like this would come.   \t          a time where you wouldnâ’t be here to explain to me â“why things happen the way they do!â” or why you go through so much nonsense while youâ’re in the system.  i never understood the system,  but he made \t things so much easier to understand.  so whom do i turn to now? who do i go to when all\t else fails? or when i feel that no one wants to hear me out.  who do i turn to instead?\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ti never understood why he was there for me.  but the more i think about it,  he knew that he was the only male figure i was close to and trusted.  i confided in him and he confided in me.  but whom do i confide in now? who can trust me enough to confide in me?\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ti donâ’t know,  but god can answer prayers and i know that heâ’s an on time god.  and heâ’ll be their right on time.

title: All For You Dad

text: so slowly ,  i watched him climb down the stair he would be gone soon ,  in my mind such a thought didnâ’t dare his face so old yet seemed so lovely all the more reasons to keep away the thoughts so ugly he is the world to me like the father the world  would ever see.   reading the newspaper and sipping his daily tea all the knowledge in his mind kept secured for only me going to work at his usual time  kept me hidden from all the dangers as sour as lime he is the meaning of life to me like the father the world would ever see.    chocolates and sweets to him are dear so much courage that he got nothing to fear tells me stories of his own childhood  with style giving me inspiration soon or  after a while he is the hero to me like the father the world would ever see.

title: Illusions Of Time
author: tarric
text: as darkness falls,  over the day                                   the light evaporates and is led astray  death,  crying,  pain,   and anger…… i pause and wonder why?,                                                                                                all                       these people starve       i stand and think and zero out the sound                                                                     of torture and despair flowing all around.   staring at the stars in the sky;                                                        ; sparkling brightly asking why?  the air grows cold,  my body shivers.  i listen to crickets chirp                                                                     under the darkness of the moon  water beginning to drip on my face                                                                   i begin to realize what will happen soon.   can it be? is it real? is it truly here?  peace,  quiet,  and happiness,  to take away all the fear  ring! ring! the alarm clock chimes,   i knew it was all too good to be true it was all a frame on a wall that was so tempting to view  but the glass is shattered and so is the dream,   now you understand that nothing is what it seems  i know the truth now,  the world will never become perfect,  it will never become real,   it will always be based on illusions and people who donâ’t feel.

title: I Wish It Was This Easy
author: tarric
text: the breeze flows through the air like an everlasting spring.  my heart beats slowly.  i can feel it pulsating.  the stacks of reality are toppling over.   the little bottle of truth  has been shattered.   its content spread across the floor,  splattered.   the tiny bottle of love has been left open for too long.   the bright light that use to shine,  and show us the way,  has now blown out from strenuous abuse.   the simple stapler that once made bonds,  has snapped in two,  from constant overuse.   the colors,  that we thought  to be everlasting,  have now ceased to exist,  because of our blindness that we could not resist.   reality,  truth,  love,  light,   some colors,  a stapler,  and a pair of glasses.   iâ’ll send the order in tonight.  it should be here tomorrow.   the supermarket of life

title: My Light
author: tarric
text: as the shores depart into the darkness there comes a voice traveling the sea.  a voice so loud no one can hear,  a voice so magical,  no one can fear.  but godâ’s will is nothing to be toyed with  as my bright shadow slips away into the sea darkness smothers,  encircles,  and captures me and takes me into its enchanted lair.  where there is no light,  nothing but despair.   i am constantly rotating around this earth but no one really cares  i am away from home i can't break free there is nowhere to go there is no one to see,   and no one to know  but in only a few hours it will all be gone i will be up again,  shining strong i thank the people who have waited so long.  i am here.  .  . i will be back,  goodbye.

title: Jiffy Puff
author: taylor
text: one day i saw a cloud  while i was standing  in a towering crowd.   i looked up and saw  what looked like my parrotâ’s jaw.  the downy,  feathery mass was all by itself except one other cloud,  off in the distance which appeared to look like the boot of an elf.   it followed me to school that day; and played with me at recess.  i was starting to think it was a little obsessed.   walking with my face in the sky,   i must have looked silly,  but i didnâ’t care,   really.

author: taylor
text: a gift from several birthdays ago,   i remember the hot pink,   glossy wrapping with the  silvery bow.  i tore through the mask of paper; scattering the remains all  across the  floor.   madeline-is what it read.   a flimsy little doll with a big yellow hat,  and hair of cherry  red.   i took it up to my room,  and placed it on my bed.   what i had really wanted was a barbie,   instead.   her blue felt coat and the small,  flannel dress smelled of pine,  for some reason; which reminded me of that autumn season  when i scraped my knee.  football was never the sport for me.    i was six then,   but i stil recall that birthday again  and again.

title: High School English
author: teagan
text: outstanding strengthening plots beautifully unconfined poetry analysing the inner workings of authors hidden messages a second home for all the imaginative writers and poets.   unanticipated misfortune looms over like a black raincloud on a sunny day bigger and badder and meaner it gets with a promise of anguish and destruction and misdirection  and just as unexpected as the trojan horse the plots are torn there are loopholes and lusts for more definition the poetryâ’s in shambles as every stanza is scrutinized word choice is poor; couldâ’ve gone deeper the roof of this second home has frozen the imagination any analysis is subjective and put up for debate  no longer a sanctuary for the gifted no longer a room full of different worlds  no.   a room,  dark and cold; only a room full of sad sacks your only way out is stepping back in line giving up your creative bone and living in fear of what once was beloved.

title: True Friendship
author: tehra
text: i know you will always be there for me to turn to.  i want you to know i will always be there and know that i will love you.  there is a thin line between love and friendship.  i believe i'm walking that thin line.  there are moments when i see you my heart does skip,  but for now friendship is just fine.  you know how to brighten my day i hope that i brighten yours too.  there aren't even enough words to say how much i love you.  the special friendship that we share all the fun times we have together i know that this kind of friendship is rare.  i hope we stay like this forever.  people say that friendship is the basis of love i know that this is true you were sent to me from up above i believe i was meant for you.  the time will come when we will share a life,  but our friendship will not end i'll get the privilege of  becoming your wife and true love will begin.

text:
there's a time and place,  for everything.  there's a reason why,  certain people meet.  there's a destination,  for everyone.  what's the explanation,  when we're done?  all the summer nights spent wondering; so many questions asked,  but no one's answering.  would it be okay if i left today? took my chances on what you said was wrong  i'm jaded,  stupid,  and wreckless.  not sorry,  and i'll never regret.  these years spent,  so faded and wreckless.  not sorry,  and i'll never regret these years.  i'll never regret these years.   now here i sit,  so far away.  remembering all our memories.  it's times like these that i miss you most,  remembering when we were so close. . . .  < i wrote=\ this=\ poem=\ last=\ year=\ in=\ my=\ english=\ class. =\ i=\ think=\ it=\ was=\ one=\ of=\ my=\ best=\ writings. !!</p=\>

title: Love's a hard game to play
author: torrie
text: wake up my sweet child,  there's something i've got to say to you tonite.  it's time you took a look inside,  see there's so much more to me than meets the eye.   well there's more to love than makin' time,  the harder you look,  the more you'll find.  it's never easy- no matter what they say.   the problem here is not fear,  the trouble is you can't convince yourself.  for tonight,  let's lose the past make love last,  put our worries up on the shelf.   we've been through thick & thin- and back again,  and we can endure love's sweet pain.  rememeber,  starting the fire is easy,  the hardest part  is learning how to keep the flame.   love's like walking a real fine line,  you get  too close and you'll go blind.  let go too long- it will drift away.   love's a hard game to play,  the heart's the price you pay,  win or lose,  no matter what they say love's a hard game to play. . .

title: Grief
author: trisha
text: you donâ’t really know it until you experienced it yourself you might see it affect friends  and so you go offer words of comfort to ease their pain but you know they are just words that cannot fully heal the wound in their heart.  but it will help it to not fester.  at the end of the day you didnâ’t really know the grief that they were going through.  a year has passed since then and now itâ’s you in that hunched over position.   with eyes so glassy they were like mirrors.   not really paying attention as to what is going on.  because you still think all of this is a dream.  but then you feel someone snap you out of your numb state.  you stare at your mother who has broken down in front of you.  clenching your black attire as she moans â“why did he have to go?â” over and over again as if saying it would bring him back and you donâ’t say anything at all,  because you donâ’t know either.

title: A Natural Grave
author: tyler
text: i am perched above the world,  staring down at the natural mirror,  there is an image  of clouds  ,  and a familiar distorted face.   the ripples carry leaves ,  roaring reds and bland browns,  occasionally a leaf with some life passes,  but then disappears into the white water.   slivers of golden sun,  piercing the embrace of gray,  allowing life to shine,  life that will soon fade away,  a red arrow,  pierces the ripples with ease,  he was a friendly looking man,  we made eye contact,  then he was taken away,  north,  the moss told me that,  it never dies.   it was an unparalleled silence.  i couldn't compare it to anything i know of.  nothing was moving,  besides the river flow which was always accountable.   autumn is an interesting death.

text: what to be,  what to be? this question comes up so frequently itâ’s like,  people want to imagine you in a position and like,  they want to judge in a your edition of like,  the dream you in your rendition of what you perceive this world to be.  well,  care i donâ’t but itâ’s got me thinking on what to do,  what to do? i can see it now how wandering minds wonder about which of the dreams  hold more purpose in reality wait! iâ’m dreaming….  iâ’ll work 200, 000 feet in the air,  controlling the sky or iâ’ll be 200 feet in the ground,  taking a train to let expensive knowledge pass me by then,  maybe then iâ’m allowed more time to chose on what to do,  what to do?  a hero,  i can be flying through the cities  with handcuffs on my wrist  and a gun on my hips not.  at violence,  i cringe.   i can still fly through the streets putting out fires between the trees no.  too unpredictable.    i can save those with pain to store working through the red-stained gore.  ew.  blood.   if my brain is capable,   defending those who are wronged freely but! are they really? so where i stand again,  how to make a decision on putting unguaranteed time in something thatâ’s not even here living is for everyone but unfortunately it doesnâ’t mean it has to be concerned about my inner turmoil itâ’s imperturbed by my fears unbothered by time.   the clock is speaking.  ticking.  warning.  tick tock  the future is incapable of waiting,  he says seconds go by he comes closer my mind still going,   what to be,  what to be?

title: Messed Up teenager
author: vanessa
text: my parents once told me,  just be yourself.  but how can i do this without any help?  i love you mom and dad,  but you just don't understand.   i'm not a messed up teenager because i want to start a band! my name it does not matter,  only what's inside.  you say that you are proud of me,  but then you run and hide.   i'm not a messed up teenager because i don't like what you wear,  the truth is mom and dad,  i really just don't care.   when people say i'm different i smile,  like it's great.  when you hear people say i'm weird,  your eyes get full of hate.    i'm not a messed up teenager because my clothes don't always match,  and i won't be a messed up teenager if i miss one quiz in math!   i love you mom and dad,  but there's something you don't see,  i'm not a messed up teenager because i watch too much t. v.    my favorite color's black,  mom.  and yah dad,  i like boys! but i'm growing up,  i'm a teenager now,  i don't want to play with toys!   i'm sorry if i don't like school,  i know it makes you mad.  and you're right,  i don't have tons of friends,  but one's not all that bad.    i'm sorry if i can't be that little girl you once thought that you knew.  but i'm not a messed up teenager because i don't like ballet,  like all the other girls in shcool.    i love you mom and dad,  but there's something you don't see,  i'm not a messed up teenager,  i'm just trying to be me!

title: The Hilltop House
author: varun
text: the hilltop house  lets walk around this empty house,  scurrying around like a small mouse.  the house stands tall like a solitary loon,  on the hilltop just below the moon.  the house has no children no wives,  no men and not even a couple of dimes.  vines are hanging around from every balcony,  occasionally one would hear a cuckoo bird casting forth its melody.  the house has been abandoned over a decade ,  and now it is considered as a headache.  its ancient structures still stand upright,  it has gone through all kinds of days and nights.  it seems as if the house is cribbing through its hollow halls,  as if narrating the chronicles of its dreadful brawls.  it used to be a sublime in its time ,  but now it is covered all over with thyme over time.  when rain pours,  the house fills like morning cup of tea,  but the rain keeps singing till it hears the house plea.  feeling guilty the rain stops,  sun shines,  wiping off every tear and making the house again sublime.  the house has grown so old,  has all his stories untold,  one day a man would come and make all the chapters unfold.  i guess i'm like that house having stories stuck inside me ,  someday someone would come and  see the real me .  i don't know will that day will come in this life or the next,  but i gonna just sit back,  relax and pray for the best.

title: What If...

title: Who is the real monster?
author: aarushi
text: i looked under my bed in the hopes of catching the boogeyman curled up for the night the vicious monster with dark circles under his eyes-that no amount of make- up could hide! crooked yellow teeth-without a doubt,  the number one on the hit list of the tooth fairy!! and that awful burnt face! made medusa appear like an epitome of beauty and grace.   we used to make fun of the boogeyman,  my friends and i laugh out loud behind his back,  sometimes even in front of him when the tall lanky man,  with the unshaven beard and a satchel in his hand-the human boogeyman would walk by.  with his eyes downcast,  satchel in hand,  he'd walk down the street.  only stopping for a moment when my friends would scream.   they would call him names,  demeaning names,  horrible names- names i dare not repeat but he would just walk by-the tall lanky man,  with the unshaven beard,  and a satchel in his hand-carrying with him,  a silent plea.   i looked into his eyes,  wearing a mask of my own the infamous smirk,  the glaring,  condescending eyes-that could bring hitler and his cronies to shame,  and crumble all their unspoken lies i looked at his repulsive face.  he stole a glance at me  all i saw-were sad,  puppy eyes.  his eyes i saw- glistened with unshed tears-like something was tearing him apart.  (i knew what it was.  oh i knew it well. ) he wasn't afraid anymore.  of staring right back at me.  he looked straight ahead that tall lanky man with the unshaven beard and a satchel in his hand.   he screamed.  he howled and screamed and howled some more like he had seen something frightening.  like he had come face to face with a mirror.   my friends-my friends-with their eyes,  popping and their paled expressions.  ran at lightning speed- away from all that they couldn't understand this reaction from the boogeyman,  was uncalled for.  and what they didn't understand,  they needn't care about only i stood,  rooted to the spot.   i watched him scream and cry and rub his eyes with the back of his hand he was a sad,  sorry wreck.  something that wasn't funny.  all the violent tales about him,  the stories i had heard- bashing up kids,  vandalizing cars he wasn't welcome even in the bars!! he used to eat out of bins-raw meat and lead and pick up a fight every now and then.  all crumbled away into dust.  lies,  all lies!!! a clever web of rumors,  deceit and lies.   is this the madman my parents had warned me about?

title: Face It!
author: ada
text: some days your life goes great  and your thankful to be alive.   other days are not so good and you feel like you can't survive.   you feel like you're drowning. . .  you just can't seem to catch your breath.   you think you're losing everything,   you feel there's nothing left.   is it not hard for you to wake each morning  knowing what you've lost?  is it not painful for you  to realize what you chose for such a cost?  how could you let your most precious treasures  slowly slip away?  just so you could have your material pleasures  throughout the day.   you turned from us  and now you've come back from this place.   and you can't quite seem  to look your mistakes in the face.   how could you come back  thinking your position would be the same?  don't you understand  that their feelings for you have changed?  can you not realize  that your acceptance will take time? my brother's love may have come easy  but it won't be the same with mine!

title: Resuming Life
author: adam
text: he tries to resume life,  he looks like he's back.  he laughs like normal,  he talks normally.   no one would be able to see the pain that he's in the pain that laughter brings him the pain that talking causes.   they try to cheer him up,  they try to joke around.  they don't understand they never will.   they give up like she did,  they stop trying and move on.  he understands that he doesn't need them he finds solace elsewhere.   reading eases his mind,  makes him feel at peace.  writing allows an outlet,  the emotions flow like a rapid current.   normally he wouldn't write,  normally he would laugh at the thought.  poetry he thought what a joke,  he wonders now if he's the joke.

title: The illusions
author: alex
text: the death of dreams dictates the outward look of life gazed in the crystal ball,  where the dreams of life are so slightly stuck,  between the folly of rise and fall.   sometimes joined by such force of tenuity the vision becomes brittle and blind,  gazing beneath the ruptured beauty life and living become combined.   above the heightened sense of affliction love and life are in perspective lost,  somehow waylaid by irksome addiction to act and cease to debate the cost.   used to define but never to master dreams are braille to the naked eye,  applied as paste in my life to plaster inane notion with prudent supply.

title: Nothing
author: alexis
text: there are no words to tell anyone how i feel no matter how hard i try i always screw up the pain,  the cries,  and no words  i can scream as loud as want,  but nothing  nothing  my heart shatters over and over  music is my place god is place  but as i cry out still nothing  nothing  i cling to what means the most to me  even then it hurts more than before it seems the pain,  the cries,  and again no words  nothing  i will cry for hours and hours  every where i go my walls are up  afraid to let anyone and everyone in  i try to but still nothing  nothing  no one understands,  they try but they don't they never will  i am trying to get better  i am trying to get rid of the pain  i am trying to forget everything  but nothing  nothing  nothing  my chest screams in pain because there is so much going on i cry out to god  where are you? is anyone even there? where are they? nothing  breathe they say  it'll be okay they say  it'll get better they say  but i feel nothing  nothing  i feel like i am doing so much better i feel like things are starting to change but then like a wave crashing on rocks  my world shattered again  and again  my heart sits shattered like broken glass  i try to pick up the pieces,  but they keep falling  still there is nothing  nothing  i listen to music  i feel the beat running through my mind and veins  like a flowing river,  the music flows through me i start to feel happiness,  but again i seem to go back  i seek help,  i am getting help but i feel nothing changing nothing  nothing  nothing  i feel destroyed like a boulder hitting a wall why does it keep hurting  i finally found peace and happiness  music and a person and god our faith together was strong,  is strong  his hand was always there to help me up  his touch was always there to wipe my pain and tears away  he showed me love and grace he showed me christ again  i found the love within my family again within me again  i thought i should die and i tried,  but i wouldn't have this if i did i try to see that i am beautiful,  but something i see nothing  nothing  i see guilt and shame  i see the bad and ugly,  not the goodness but they help me see the good  they help me see the grace and forgiveness i hit a rock in my life,  like a train crashing the flood gates have opened,  everything is pouring out but nothing seems to be happening,  but pain  nothing  what exactly is this nothing? i donâ’t even know,  but one day i wonâ’t have to know it anymore one day i will finally be at full peace with god by my side,  i will be ok with him by my side,  i will be happy with them by my side,  i will have support and with me,  my heart will be full a little broken and cracked,  but full the nothing will everything and something  something  something  something  i am beautiful i am not afraid anymore  hurt? yes,  but this will all pass this is my fight,  but power will come back no one has control over my shame and guilt anymore  no one has a say in what i wear,  or look like anymore no one has a say in my life except god i am a daughter of god  i am loved  i am forgiven  i am home i am broken,  but brave i am bruised,  but this is who i am  this is my life,  my story,  this is the real me  i love smiles,  and laughs  i love helping others,  in a sense it helps me when i canâ’t help myself,  i help others and the nothing,  becomes something  something  there is something there  thereâ’s a spark and the spark is growing  i will be a light again  i can not wait for the day i look back on this i can not wait for the day i don't have to worry anymore  i will be okay  i am strong  stronger than i have ever been before  no more nothing,  its time for something  today is my day,  today is the day  i will rejoice and be glad because today i am still breathing  i am still loved and loving  i am still smiling and laughing i am not out of those yet it is not time for me to be called to my real home yet this is my home and i love it this is my something  something  turning into everything and this is the end  the end to my new beginning  with god,  family and them at my side there is my home and my love

title: A Perfect Fall Day
author: alice
text: a cool breeze rolls through the air  softly nudging clouds on their journey.  the breeze gently encourages vibrant red leaves  to fly as if they were young cardinals.  the clouds move aside to make room for the joy of the sun who softly touches flowers to make them glow with beauty student leisurely walk after a long day of filling their minds with knowledge.  and geese quietly honk their way to warmth, but occasionally dropping down to enjoy  a perfect fall day

title: A Road to Anywhere
author: allison
text: one day,  we'll keep driving forward,  and we'll take the road to anywhere.  we'll travel the world,  and i'll stick my head out the window like my dog always does.  i'll hear a symphony of horns as we pass through the city.  i'll have the aroma of the ocean fill up my nose,  and give me a feeling of pure happiness.  we'll see miles and miles of nothing,  and it will be beautiful.  when we stop in the arctic i'll reach down and touch the snow,  and go back to my days of building snowmen.  but for now,  we'll sit here and watch tv,  and it will be just as magnificent because i'm with you.

title: The Things That I love and Hate
author: amanda
text: i love being with my man.  cuddling kissing and holding his hand.  i love is when he says,  ''i love you. '' i smile and say,  ''i love you too. '' what more is there to do?   i hate when he leaves me.  i hate that he went away.  but what can i really say? look at what he has now become.  a soldier and the best man he can be.   i hate not knowing what he is doing.  or even if he is okay.  i know that i have to trust him.  but he is just so far away.   i love him and i miss him.  and i cant wait for him to come home.  i really do miss you honey. . .  can you please please just come home?

title: Summer
author: amanda
text: summer is on its way.   the sun is shining bright.   the smell of the fresh air.   soon it will be time to relax.   laying outside,   with the warm sun rays,   releasing all my stress for the day.   bringing a smile to my face.   blue sky,   not a rain cloud in sight.   so calming.   i can just go outside,   stare at the clear,  blue sky,   and bright,  magnificent sun.   if my day is going bad,   i just have to take a step,   out of the darkness,   and into the light.   with the beautiful land around me.   but as the sun goes down,   a marvelous painting begins to show,   with bright,  vivid colors,   forming in the sky.   the golden sun slips away.   the sky,   now black as can be.   with a spectacular glowing crescent,   craters in sight.   surrounded by bright shining stars,   twinkling through the night,   some set free,   and soar a way,   never to come back again,   but still,   many are here to stay,   to glimmer until the sun rises again.   summer i canâ’t wait for you to arrive!

title: Better Days
author: amber
text: i cry myself to sleep ,  everynight i dream ,  that the next day will be better .  another night alone ,  and another night i cry .  please show me the way  to the better days .   i hide it all away ,  waiting for those better days.  please don't leave me here alone .  please don't take away my home .  i hide it all away ,  waiting for the better days .   where did it all go wrong ,  why can't everyone just get along ? why can't we just love one another ? why do we bring each other so much pain? why can't we just go back to the better days ?  i will be okay ,  but i miss the better days .  i hide it all away ,  trying to hide the past .  i miss those better days ,  but they never seem to last .  please show me the way to the better days . . . . .

title: You Can't Hide
author: amber
text: a rose in my hand ,  your picture in my locket ,  over your grave i stand ,  with tissues in my pocket .  my life will never again feel real .  i'm going to miss you forever .  everyone is telling me how to feel ,  and trying to make me feel better .  i just want to be alone  but nobody will go away .  i want to be in my bedroom in my home .  so,  i can slowly get though this day by day .  my head hurts but i can't cry .  my eyes will hold no more tears .  everyone tells me i'll be fine ,  but we had so many years .  your last days will always be with me.  the cries of others i still hear .  when i remember i shed a million tears .  i was so young ,  but i know what was  going on .  i know where you went and the day you died .  i know forever you'll be gone ,  so,  writing this will help me to say my good-bye . . . .

title: Courage
author: angie
text: if courage were a color,  it would be white.   as pale as a cloud behind the stars covering the dark sky behind it.  obscuring everything,  including the nervousness.  if courage were a taste it would be stale as a pear.  taking the taste and spreading it,  devouring it through every being around you.  if courage were a feeling,  it would be confidence as iâ’d tell the one how i feel.  i anxiously wait for the disappointment to wash over me,  but it never came.  if courage were a smell,  it would be as strong as a rose.  people wondering about the smell lingering around and the reason is being me.  i muster all the bravery and take a stand.  no one stopping me in the process,  probably the smell hanging around.  if courage were a sound,  it would be the beating of a drum in an orchestra.   its music echoing through the earth reminding others of its stability and assuredness.  reminding me,  i am not alone,  there is someone who cares.   experiencing a feeling of power after everything i went through.

title: Hope
author: angie
text: if you hold on too long youâ’ll get hurt. \t youâ’ll get blinded through its lies and misunderstandings.   taking you nowhere but into the oblivious,  a mysterious voice calling out to you.  crushing everything you've ever come to love,  blowing out the flare that warms your heart.  freezing it and shattering into a million pieces.  brings down the world into a never ending war,  two sides always arguing.  one side wanting darkness and the other side light.  unable to decide because you give up and think there isn't another way.  yourself going insane,  regretting everything you've done it is a continuous labyrinth of moods that collect scars along the way.   unsure if youâ’re going to be happy again.  broken promises,  hearts,  and lives because of hope.  although everything is unexpected youâ’ll keep desiring hope.  chasing you towards the beginning of the labyrinth,  starting all over again

title: Lost
author: angie
text: blood stained the walls and arms of the sad weeping child.  red covered its eyes,  lips,  and cheeks.  leading its being through a dark path into the void,  with nothing but mere hope.  the shadows swallowed everything into the darkness.  it consumed the child and roamed the earth.  \t leaving the only light in its path was a spark of the stars above head.   the child was afraid of falling into slumber knowing that maybe it would be its last.  every night it would plead its final end,  knowing that life would get worse.  the poor childâ’s eyes screamed death; youâ’d look at them and see nothing but a pure dark,  black stare.  it lingered around as a shadow gaining nothing but dark thoughts.  soon the child began to see a light,  something unimaginable.   walking close to it at times but then backing away from it,  afraid of starting all over again.  instead deciding to stay because of what the shadow has done to you and no oneâ’s there to help you out.   at some point the small light began to get brighter,  bigger,  and the feeling of warmth.  is there really a reason to be happy?

title: Tartarus

text: as luminous helios forsakes his throne in the sky,  the dreary moon rises,  the earth runs dry.  at the precipice of sanity where few men have gone,  each day new evils and new spectres are born.  itâ’s paths are strewn with mountains of bone,  itâ’s rivers resound with anguishâ’d groans.  beneath the crimson rock that stretches oâ’er this land,  a fiery spleen slumbers,  child of fateâ’s dark hand.  emaciated corpses crawl along itâ’s streams,  cauldrons of sorcerers boil,  conjuring nightmarish dreams.  and torrid clouds thunder in bloodstainâ’d skies; he who ventures there,  pitiless dies.  trust not the ground upon which thou walkâ’st,  trust not the ghouls that wander in the dark.  if ever man spoke of virtue or good deed,  â‘twas black as lie can be; evil has no heed.  venture into the seething abysses of hellâ’s burning deeps,  and behold the smoldering gorgon,  malevolent scourge that sleeps.

text: every now and then we hear it  the sound of silence it's in us now isn't it  everthing now is in silence   evrything loud then silent  no matter what we do  nothing can be permanently silent  it will eventually come to you  even if we try it'll never stay  even at night there's still a buzz  with all the noise nothing is put away  even through the days of the week theirs a buzz  i would cry to hear the silence  even if i ment my life  i want to hear the silence  i need it in my life   many people get the silence  but only when they try  why don't we get silence  i guess i'll only know when i die    now fifty-two years have past i don't know how much time is left  my friends have already past  i cannot deny the facts to my left   now i am alone  with nothing to do  now i've only got a clone  and i can only watch time you too   i can only wait for my day  to come on by  many try to help in my way  but i'm always there ready to die   waiting my life away  i cry for silence  withering away  i finally achieved silence   but with the cost of my life  the best stopped in my chest  i flew away without my life  i can now have eternal rest   i can now live a life of silence  their is nothing but silence

title: Happy Birthday

text: i loathe this time of year a time intended for celebration but instead i detest all i hear is â“happy birthdayâ”  from strangers with perky smiles  i cringe at every syllable \t another year  a whole year older why do we have this outdated ritual? why do we continue to mark getting close to the end? we rejoice something rotten with something as sweet as cake  we indulge in a big chocolate cake  with countless pink and blue candles and sugary white frosting we sing this juvenile song at the top of our lungs all to masquerade our true feelings of it  we take a deep breath and blow out the candles  grinning when we blow it out in one try  we make a wish playing along with the imaginary pretending as we always have

title: I Shout My Name
author: benji
text: i shout my name,  and what he hears is a word but what he sees is a painting of my life my flaws louder than my achievements my regrets bolder than my triumphs my weaknesses stronger than my strengths  my body is inverted to him my mind in front of my hair my heart in front of my chest my physical appearance hidden behind my soul  and there is barely enough room for all of me on the canvas this is myself,  and my painting,  and how he sees me is how i was created to be seen and how i created myself to be seen my actions are my own and when they affect others they affect me just as much  my secrets become my first impression and i am not ashamed of them i stamp my name on each and every one of them why should i care if someone admires a mask if it is not my own?  i drown my picture with dark shades and i highlight spots with a warm bright yellow but never do i dare mix the two why paint over the spots where the brush in my hand slips? the spots would live on under the new layer of paint never erased,  but covered and out of sight so i do not remember not to slip my hand again  i shout my name! i display depth in a two dimensional picture i speak secrets in a silent,  wordless frame i create darkness without black paint and white when i mix colors  i admire myself,  and i see the full painting,  and i know my name

title: Untitled
author: beth
text: i was walking alongside the road when i heard music coming from the car the silver car with the windows down and the driver she was tall and had chocolate hair wind whipped and curly blowing across her face her cherry lips and untamed eyes and skin of peaches and cream she was not beautiful but she was magnificent in her plainness her perfect candor inspired by the day called out to me as she sang  voice of an angel no not that  but something free and something chained sprang out of her song freed in the springtime air and what she sang no one could say perhaps it was a song that she made up herself she was free and she was boundless emancipated liberated enlightened she was free and she was bound but something chained sprang out in song her wild accompanist and though there  was nothing splendid in her face except her untamed eyes there was a constrained independence in her song i fell in love with that  perfect imperfection and as she drove by i knew i would never see her again but then again i might in the constrained freedom of a springtime afternoon.

title: Praise Poem

text: my eyes are the bullets that pierce through your skin.  they can see you before you see yourself.  my eyes will not only get your attention; but will make you pay attention to me.   if you want to try to fight this glare: go ahead,  but be  ready to lose.  my eyes are green with gold.  when iâ’m ready for you,  theyâ’ll let you know.   not one man can outsmart these eyes.  these eyes will chew you and spit you back out.  hypnosis mixed with brainwashing to the maximum.  my eyes are pretty powerful.   these eyes hit you like the first raindrop.  impossible to not know where it came from yet,  giving the knowledge that the storm is soon to come.   i may not ever throw a fast punch.  but these eyes of mine will put you in the hospital.
