title: Your just hiding the pain
author: chelsea
text: behind your eyes i see the pain.  as i make you travel down memory lane.  i donâ’t know how youâ’ve managed to keep sane.  you keep a smile through the sun and the rain.   your just hiding the pain,  i donâ’t understand why you tell me thereâ’s nothing wrong.    when clearly there is,  with your face so sad.  explain what happened that was so bad.  you make me wonder is it because you're so mad.  i miss the days we were happy,  glad.   your just hiding the pain,  help me to understand what happened.   you say you were hurt when you was young ,  we all trip and fall.  you cant possibly be so upset over that,  that cant be all.  i remember that day you got that call.  your face was a picture it said it all.   your just hiding the pain,  so youâ’ve explained.   i never got it before but now i do.  abused,  neglected that really happened to you.  i cant believe i didnâ’t realize we're like glue.  together forever me and you.   you're just hiding the pain,  i understand now what happened.   i am glad we're friends and i'll help you through.  because now i know what happened i'll do all i can do.  to always be there and always be true.  i'll never know how it felt to be you.   your still hiding the pain,  just let it go.   let's be happy again,  skipping around.  i miss the times weâ’d make those squeaky sounds.  i miss the times weâ’d run for ages making are hearts pound.  and then your happiness just drowned.   your still hiding the pain,  listen to my words.   remember those days when we played that game.  and went to the cinema and watched fame.  we used to run round the seats i know it was lame.  that was us its just a shame.   youâ’ve stopped hiding the pain,  now i can smile with you.   now do you realize i have suffered too.  iâ’ve missed my friend and most of all iâ’ve missed you.  and now i have your laughter,  i love to watch the silly things you do.  together forever were stuck like glue.

title: The earth has drowned
author: chelsea
text: the storm came and swept through the broken land.  i looked down on the earth, water covered the sand.  no grass, no green, just blue, blue the sea.  i thought to myself,  no way this cannot be.  the world encased.  we did not solve the problem we faced.  now look. flooded, dead, the human race.  the end of the world seemed so far,  yet near.  yet now the worlds fate is clear.  how i long to see, the future.  whats left for me.  i wish now i had died with the rest! watching them die,  slowly drowned! down, down they sink to the bottom of the sea.  i didn't understand or didn't take notice, how could this be.  the day the earth drowned.  the silence, no sound.  fingers in ears. head in my lap.  the country drowned, we'll be needing a new map.  no life, no cries, no more, no life on earth.  for earth has drowned.

title: Big Shade Tree

title: The Quiet Within the Noise
author: christina
text: breathe,   inhale… exhale… like the parting of seas inhale… exhale… so quiet,  is the room in which i sit.  nothing but an ivory chair,  and four stark white walls,  emptiness.   all breathing in slow pulses.   but it is not the walls that exhibit small life,  no,  they are just matter of unfeeling properties.   static noise is all i can hear now,   overwhelming my thought processes.  â“no! no!â” i scream,  but everything is too serene.  what is happening to me? like the quiet in the noise,  i could never fill the void.   like an atom being split,  my mind is unwinding.  no longer binding,  i could never grasp what little i had to feel when i was real,  or alive.  am i just dead inside?

title: ONCE THE GUARD FADES, SUMMER IS HERE
author: danielle
text: the sun like a fire with no heat.  glowing in the blue delight.  fading to magenta,  - a farmerâ’s nightmare,  yet so striking to the eye.  the leafless trees painted like back shadows against the bright blue skies above.  the cold winters breeze,  makes our hairs stand tall,  the bumps in our skin arise.   a guard blocking the fire,  refusing to shed heat until the time is right.  the first day of summer finally arrives.  the guard seems to fade.  finally the fire that once had no heat -warms up what seems to us the whole world.   our jackets fall off,  we roll up our sleeves.  the only time in the year,  no guilt id felt for lying around.  no chores being fulfilled .  no movement within the people around.  laziness takes over our bodies.  still no guilt.  we fry our skin like ham in the oven.   the last day is hear.  our cells start moving.  we feel the need to move from our frying spots.  preparing for the next season.  our jackets back on,  or sleeves rolled down.  the guard again,  blocking the heat .  until once more,  the time is right.

title: What Is True Love

title: Untitled
author: deanna
text: no memory of this unhappy place.  it burns under my skin like a thousand tatoos all over the body.   you either fit in or you don't.  there is no in between the social party.  you are categorized by the outside,  not the inside.  no one cares for the real you anymore.   it has to be hidden deep down in the heart until you lose who you really are.   there is no unmasking it after its gone.  there is no help to resurface what has melted away from your grasp.  new people will try to reconstruct you to fit the new standards.  you follow along but inside you know they are far off.  inside you are secretly crying for help and no one can hear you.  you are too afraid to let anyone hear your pain.  no medicine will aid the burning fire flaming in your stomach.  balling up in a small corner seems to be the only aide that calms it for awhile.  and as you are balled up,  you see the other side of all this turmoil.  all you have to do is stand up for yourself.  be the real you that you lost so long ago.  look them in the face and say ''i am me and thats all i will ever be.  handle it or leave me alone. ''

title: Grandfather
author: destini
text: grand father  you were always the best to me  you always cared.   always spoiled me.    not only with gifts.   but with love.    grandfather.   why did you fight?  we knew it would take you.   we knew no matter how hard you fought you would leave…   grand father  the disease took you  but we still have your love  and we still have your memories.    iâ’ll never forget the day you took me to get my first fishing pole   you got it then you took me and you lost it in the lake  i forgive you grandfather.   i was with you.    i had your love.    i had your time.    grandfather.   why did you take me in?  i wasnâ’t yours by blood.   but you still took me in.    grandfather.   you arenâ’t here.   but thank you.    i wish there could still be the days when  i could wake you up with breakfast in bed  i could wake you with the dog licking your face.    grandfather  why didnâ’t you fight more?  why didnâ’t you prove us all wrong?  you shouldâ’ve fought the disease  more…   i was too young to lose you.   you were the man i knew as  grandfather and at times you were my dad.   why didnâ’t you fight?   we all miss you.   you caused a great deal of pain for us all.    yes we have the memories.   we have the times spent together.    but i want to feel your touch again.   i want to hear the startup of your truck before  we went fishing.   i want to light fireworks with you again.    itâ’s a lot to wish for you back.    but iâ’d give anything to speak with you again.   to hear your voice.    at least one more time.    one more time of the unconditional love you had for me.   i want to hear you calling my name.    i can not get these things back.   but i keep pictures.   i have them all over my room.   i still have the bear you took me to get.   i still have everything you ever got me.    i sleep with the bear.   i feel itâ’s all i have left of you   there isnâ’t a day that goes by  that i donâ’t think of you.    grandfather.   youâ’re my savior.   youâ’re my hero.   if it werenâ’t for you and how you raised me  i wouldnâ’t be the young lady i am now.     grandfather.     you shouldnâ’t have fought so long.   it wouldnâ’t have been so painful for you  grandfather.     i love you.   but why did you fight so long?

title: Who We Are

text: among us are people,   quite as a brook or as fierce as a tide some are bold,  some are wild  and some exceptionally wild.   every soul is extravagant in a way fresh as dew which shines like pearl and resolute as the basking sun which sets in the golden bay.   everyone is in this world for a cause,  either sacred or sad.  to scrutinize a distinct mystery of life we couldn't have.   so stop sulking over petty defects.  stop crying and causing pain to others.  and remember! our differences made us who we are.   strange,  not at all.  special that's what we are.

title: The Prince's Parade
author: diana
text: once upon a time in a kingdom far away lived a prince who was. . .  picky,  shall we say.   now the prince had a birthday and a parade was planned,  with jugglers and minstrels and everything grand!  the king's baker made a cake that was ten feet tall.  while the queen's ladies-in-waiting wrapped presents large and small.   animals were brought from distant lands.  like tigers and zebras and even orangutans.   streamers were hung in the streets galore,  but the young prince  still wanted more.   the prince screamed for the duke who came running to his side,  where he found the prince with a grin rather wry.

title: Under the gleaming moon
author: dilliram
text: under the white moon as usual dawa sat under the comforting hillock of an old willow tree.  the tears cascaded   from the weakened eyes through the pale cheeks.  it was the quit late twilight and the waxing moon slowly came up to its reign,  he felt soothing comfort under the embrace of the mighty glowing friend and slowly and with much of care he picked up a stone and with his left hand just as he have learnt from his beloved mom he threw the stone to nearby pond and the ripple continued………. .  it was first day of his college and with destiny in his hand he had gone to eastern bhutan for engineering course.  the life took other way and he fell under the treacherous claws of the destiny.  just like many middle class family of his school he too was from that back ground for which the history of bhutanese is reveled.  never in his  life   he faced any lows as he was completely brought up with utmost care and love by his most trusted uncle.  with  influence from his friends he was dragged by the company of drugs ad became addicted to it and the time also came that he could not live without the intoxication of drugs.  one day a friend of his took his school bag and he fortunately returned it back as several time he had never returned.  but soon he was called to the office and the principal started to check his bag.  alash! he found several packets of n10  in his bag.  it was not his but in what ever way he tried to convince the principal he did not listened and he became frustrated and gave a blow! to  principle.  next day police came and took him you the prison. .  but today he regrets those days which he spent with drugs and tells.  â”drugs gave me wings to fly but it took away my wings to fly.

title: ''Do you Hear?''

text: do you hear the silent weeping? their moans are sung so low.  and anyone who tries to help them are marked by all they know.   do you hear the lonely crying? their piercing screams that seem undying truth that streams from the undenying its the pain that fuels their tears.   do you hear the voice of sadness? the ongoing struggles with the unimaged.  the constant shame you couldn't fathom.  its the madness,  taking its toil.   and do you hear the worn away? the things they try to say.  cause if you even tried to listen their thoughts would turn you gray.

title: We Will Stand Last

text: we will stand last by: dorothy â“doraâ” s  awaking to the morning blast,  he took a vow; â‘we will stand lastâ’.  heâ’s out to fight,  and win the gold,  loyal to his country; he wonâ’t be sold.   every morning it is the same,  itâ’s a battlefield; not a videogame.  lives are lost and bodies forgotten,  he wonders if itâ’s all too often.   a part of him; little,  it may be,  knows the war isnâ’t being fought properly.  â“deaths occur,  life goes on; no need to mope!â” he tries his best not to lose hope.   loyal he is,  a conscience he has,  but the two donâ’t flow,  itâ’s nothing like jazz.  nonetheless,  heâ’ll fight â‘till death,  use all his strength,  every last breath.   torn between loyalty and good sense,  he put his country first and stood his defence.  he wonâ’t go home until all is done,  until his country is proud theyâ’ve won.   another morning,  another blast,  a vowâ’s reality,  they all stood last.  he won the fight,  took home the gold,  loyal to his country,  he wasnâ’t sold.

title: A Broken Mirror
author: elijah
text: me.  who could i be? a great question to ask,  only problem is that could and am are an eternity away.  so who am i then? is it healthy to ask? is it safe to peer deeply at oneself? perhaps no,  but iâ’m not healthy enough to keep from attempting.  you see,  iâ’m a bit of a trainwreck at the moment,  my life has collapsed in a dozen ways,   iâ’ve breathed a dozen dying breaths.  from the days gone not far enough by,  iâ’ve learned too many things.  about myself,  and who i am.  about how the world sees things.  iâ’m prideful,  not merely a little so,  pride is what many know me for,  and know me to be as well.  i use what iâ’m good at to mask my flaws,  throw my accomplishments in others faces so they donâ’t notice my cracks.  but on the occasion that my pride falls flat,  i donâ’t like what i see.  iâ’m an idiot,  though not in all senses of the word,  most of my stupidity is a result of assuming i know much more than i do.  though iâ’ve learned how ignorant i am,  i still assumed iâ’m smart.  turning a blind eye to the obvious and turning my brain off should be taboo,  but society seems to accept you if you know a few facts.  iâ’m lonely,  and deeply so.  no matter how much someone really does understand,   somehow i still find a way to retain my isolation.  i grab for a hand,  go in for a kiss,  because i think thatâ’s a connection,  but deep down i feel no one knows me,  or loves me.  iâ’m angry,  and try to hide it.  throwing weights into the air until my arms have lost their strength,  then ten more times because maybe if i break myself iâ’ll stop.  they call me a good actor because i can show anger,  but itâ’s not acting when all you have to do is let a little more out.  iâ’m a liar,  because the truth is too hard to cope with iâ’m a competitor,  because maybe if i win iâ’ll feel better iâ’m a â‘perfect studentâ’ because itâ’s expected of me iâ’m a rebel,  for no reason at all iâ’m an angsty teenager who canâ’t get over themselves iâ’m a singer who canâ’t sing well enough iâ’m a musician whoâ’s not patient enough to play iâ’m an athlete who wants excellence,  but is only average iâ’m an actor whoâ’s better at portraying negative emotions because theyâ’re more familiar iâ’m a stereotype,  who knows everything theyâ’re writing is a rehash.  iâ’m broken on the inside… but so is everyone else.  is there some secret that iâ’m missing then? or is everyone else as good at hiding as i am.  this i may never know,  as i stare into a broken mirror,  reflecting back a thousand shards of a â‘normalâ’ life.

title: One More Time
author: ethan
text: shattered torn apart,  left to rot in a unholy paradise thinking of how people really were,  nice,  kind,  willing to aid you in any en-devour now im laying here,  torn apart eternally.   i imagine what if no one was here,  if i was alone,  i wouldn't be happy but i would realize a crucial fact that humans destroy what they work so hard to build.  walking down these barren streets alone,  while the chilling wind blows.   not stopping for anything necessary just continuing down my path,  soon i'll reach my destination,  my end.  what scares me is what i shall find.  cause i see the people i use to know.   so nice,  kind,  willing to aid you in any en-devour.  then i shall wake,  return to this sick reality.  then i'll my lay my head to rest and pray,  that i can fall asleep one more time,  to dream of the people i use to know,  one last time.

title: America Lost When You Died

title: War During Spring
author: heidi
text: ah,  the feel of spring in the air,  i love the springtime it's so beautiful and refreshing,  the plants and flowers are just coming up,  and the people trade their winter blues for spring time sonnets,  people shed their winter coats and sour faces for t-shirts and happy smiles,  but this spring is different,  i don't understand why did president bush decide to do this? he wrecked my happy season of spring,  he massacred the idea of spring and all the reasons i like spring,  instead of the plants coming up,  they are being trampled by heavy combat boots as the soldiers rush off to their training,  instead of people's mood changing for the better,  everyone is constantly depressed,  because of what they see,  people have shed their winter coats,  but what about their inner winter coats? sadly,  they have kept these clothes on,  and it will be many months possibly years before they can shed their inner winter coats,  all because of this thing called war,  it wasn't my decision to go fight this war,  or yours,  it wasn't the decision of the thousands of young men and women fighting in iraq,  these young people wanted to join the guard because they wanted money for college,  or to gain a great traveling exprience,  i ask you,  what kind of traveling experience do you get from seeing nothing but sand,  and seeing your comrades dying in front of your eyes? what kind of money do you get for kiling another human being? the answer is deceptively simple,  you don't,  people may agrue that this war is going well,  that we will catch saddam,  but i ask you,  how well are we really doing? what about the twelve or thirteen p. o. w. 's in iraq,  or the two people who are m. i. a. 's? does that mean we are doing well in this war if we have hostages and people missing? i don't think so,  why did we have to go and wreck spring? what happened to the simple beauty of nature? what happened to people exchanging their sour moods for smiles? what happened to shedding our coats for t-shirts? what happened to the fresh spring air we used to breathe? where did all of these things go? i'll tell you what happened,  we went to war with iraq,  now we have been at war for six days,  what have we accomplished from all this? did we learn nothing from our past mistakes,  did we not see what we did in vietnam was horribly wrong? what's wrong with our president,  did he not see the gray areas that came with the war in vietnam? apparently not,   did he not see how the people in the u. s.  protested their own soldiers? did he not see the war torn vietnam veteran who returned from the horrors of war,  and they were only thirty years old,  what has happened to our nation? is anybody pro-peace? i don't know anymore,  i have an opinion,  and i think this war is wrong,  but alas,  i'm only a seventeen-year-old girl with an opinon and nothing more,  no one else cares that this war is going to tear our country apart,  i don't know what to think anymore,  in this time of war during springtime,  no one realizes what irreparable damage this war will have on us,  in this time of war and springtime.

title: My skin like a poem
author: imani
text: the skin iâ’m in is breathless and beautiful.   no matter the color,  no matter the freckle,  scar,  or bruise.  there is no skin like mine.   my skin has been hugged,  loved,  and touched.  i've had time with my skin,  17 whole years with my skin.   you should know by now that my skin doesn't want your skin.  you should know that my skin tells a story that only i can tell.   i find it important that we take care of our skin  tell ourselves it's ok to be our skin.  tell our skin to be dumb sometimes,  to love sometimes,  and absolutely strive sometimes.  that's why my skin is me.  so sorry but my skin doesn't need you!

title: How could I choose?
author: isabel
text: how could i choose,  to leave? to go beyond these fears,  into what sent me here? how could i ignore my perceptions,  of lifeâ’s cruel,  twisted intentions? clear but unnoticed,  loud but unspoken,  and somehow so strong,  stubborn,  unbroken.  oozing like thick black tar,  unfolding like a hostile murder,  leaving jagged trails,  a scar,  forever there and forever swept,  beneath unfinished rugs of memories kept,  yet left to wither and dry,  till death,   lifeâ’s true colors are lies well met.   these cluttered thoughts,  they imprison me here.  rusty chains of love and desire,  i fear,  days go by,  each minute,  each hour,  abandons me.   lying,  guilty,  a grotesque tower,  of wilting,  unwanted,  rotting leaves,  fallen from termite ridden trees,  under a sky cloaked in grey days of old,  whose timeless arms stretch far and cold,   lifeâ’s intentions twist and fold.   for it is here,  i find myself.  drowning in forests of sorrow and doubt.  the branches grasp me by my throat,  and smother my desperate,  silent shout.  pulling me deeper into blissful dreams,  away from life and all its cruel actualities.  this place prevents and allows me to breath,  two different breaths,  two different realities.   lifeâ’s consequences enforce false mentalities  so how could i choose,  to leave? to go beyond these fears,  into what sent me here? both doors ominous,  distrustful,  and covered,  in a shadow of what may be,  a shadow of what could be,  both real and surreal,  in ways that so differently appeal,  my young mind and soul wants one,  and my future,  another.  how could i choose,  to leave?

title: Never Lose Sight
author: jason
text: i can never lose sight of who i am now. .  the person that i am can never take a bow. .  my life has brought undeniable truth. .  to those who know me,  take the red pill not blue. .  never lose sight of what you know to be true. .  always chose good over bad. .  and your life will flourish to. .  to the person you are,  open up to life. .  make your mistakes so you can get them right. .  i thought i had this life in my hand. .  come to find out,  love had blinded this man. .  i lost sight of who i once became. .  the person she loved,  i ceased blame. .  with all sight gone,  i ran a muck. .  taking for granted her love,  i am such a schmuck. .  with my sight gone,  i committed those tasks. .  that forever bared me from her loving grasp. .  out of this pain i gained a new light. .  one brighter then the sun. .  as she was my sun light. .  with mistakes made and the tides a turn. .  i must never give up on what i have learned. .  good and truth will guide my way. .  until the day i can finally say. .  my sight has come back. .  i know this to be true. .  it will never leave me. .  as long as i remember you. . .

title: What a life
author: jazzmine
text: the ups,  the downs,   the mountains high  the valleys low.   the oceans deep,   the rivers wide.   what a life,  and yes i survived.   through the storm,  and the rain  dwelling in the sickness  suffering with pain.   having tears here,   and a smile there.   a broken heart,  but no mender there.   always hurt,  scarred for life.   over the hills i have come,   so many battles i had to fight.   loving god,  and putting him first.   what a life.   i want to go in reverse  today and claim,  my battle is yet won.   my victory is yet to come,   this fight has just begun.   a blessing here,   deliverance there.   what a life.   no more misery,   so much less to bare.   ''what a life''

title: Maybe One Day
author: jean-claude
text: maybe one day by: jc   the lyrics,  they pour out to paper whenever i think of you.   i grab my guitar and sing my story of all things i wish we could do.   i wish there was a way we could just leave,  leave this crazy world of chaos and tragedy.   i promise sweetheart,  it will be just you and me.   strangers,  they wonder why we do the things we do?  simply because they canâ’t see the invisible ring of insanity that surrounds us when weâ’re in love,  they have not one clue.   our love canâ’t be summed up by some stupid clichã©  iâ’ll prove it,  iâ’ll buy your favorite chocolate and bouquet  they say love is just a game and i can see the finish line is just around the bend  i'll just press pause and our love will never end  i would die for you,  not metaphorically,  literally i would.   sometimes i wish i showed it more then i should.   i think about you every single day  i admit it; iâ’m scared,  that maybe one day you wonâ’t feel the same way.   well guess what,  that day has come,  the day i lost my shine `i threw everything i had at you,  every word; every line  everything i tried it just wasnâ’t enough  i hoped everyday that maybe i could call your bluff.   i watch as you move on with your life,  the life you chose instead  never look back,  cause iâ’m down but not dead.   because love isn't about fencing ourselves in,  feeling safe,  feeling sure about the future.  it's about scaring every nerve in our body,  but pushing forward anyway.   but i just canâ’t push anymore; consider this my farewell and my goodbye.   maybe one day you will realize how much you really meant to me  maybe one day you will realize what you could never see.

title: Dreaming

text: i dream of an art so transparent that you can look through and see the world for what it is.  when you look through it,  you see something that no one else has seen.  you see what you want to see,  no one else can tell you what to see.  no man nor woman can tell you what to say or do.  you are you and you are the only one who can be you.  you are the boss of yourself and no one else is your boss.  you can look at a piece of art and see something that is more magnificent than any other piece.  you can see something in a picture that captivates you and only you.  you see what you want to see.

text: it's fast pace,  and intense the game we play,  we practice for it day after day.   passing,  dribbling,  running and scoring in a different way,  we pay no attention to what the other people say.   it's boring,  it's slow,  why would you play,   are some of the things we here with each passing day.   you stink,  your pathetic,  your never going to win.  we'll get better each game we play over and over again.   were new,  were unexperienced,  well get better,  we may even one day receive an unexpected letter.   as you can see the put downs and criticism,  well to us it's only a clichã©.   for everyone needs practice,  and at some point in time,  like we are now we will be just fine.

title: The Immigrant
author: jesus
text: we all have dreams an immigrant leaves to meet his needs.  he wants no more hunger or suffering.  there is no more waiting in things to get worse.   heading to america,  so-called land of the free.  hides and hopes to have no misery.  turns out it's not for the free and it's nothing like it seemed to be.  he can't get a job because he's illegal.  but why? if we are all equal.   america should be america once again.  a man left his country from false promises.  risked his life to come where? the land of the free.  where we deny and crush his dream.  we all have dreams.

title: A drop Of You
author: jesus
text: a drop of you flows out of me,  seeping through  the walls of my imagination.  forming an ocean,  that engulfs and drowns creativity altogether.   a drop of you flows out of me,  fabricating words into a passion and passion into an obsession.  shaping and twisting each word,  over and over again,  until they spell out desires only you can conceive.   a drop of you flows out of me,  tainting words and  filling them with sadness,  until they overflow,  and their meaning disappears.   contamination that stains,  keeping my mind impure.  a drop of you will always just be,  another drop in the ocean.

title: Imagine

text: i thought you would not be lost,  i just thought.  i thought we'd always be with you,  but did you leave me and come up? we're away,  i hope we will meet again.  every time before,  you always have my mind.  what can you do now? hopefully you will be happy where you are.  your voice sounds like a good music,  your smile and eyes remind me.  is there any fun now with you? hopefully,  he will appreciate and keep you.  choose what makes you happy,  'it's always been over.  for the luck you love,  because you know that someone loves you,  but he still has your choice.  i hope he will keep you,  just as i feel like you're close to me.  i wrote 'to it because to say goodbye to you,  but,  as you know,  somehow i was happy for you.  hopefully over the years i'll never forget you,  because sometimes i fought my feelings.  i hope that you will not share,  imagine that i'm also hurt.  you choose the person who loves you really,  that's what makes you feel unparalleled.  the night is deepening and as far as i'm concerned,  tonight,  you're the only one in my mind.  in your embrace i'm excited,  i'm overwhelmed when we can get it back.

title: Winning or Losing!!!
author: jon
text: winning and losing is part of the game,  how you play it is all the same.  if you win you should not brag,  for if you lose you should not be sad.  if you win you could always lose,  for if you lose you could always win.  therefore do not brag or be sad,  there is always tomorrow to win or lose.  winning and losing is part of the game,  so how you play it is just your way!

title: Angel of the Night
author: joseph
text: a maiden,  hidden just beneath the grand oak,  resting upon sleeves of bark.  suddenly,  she arises,  trumpet at hand,  a beautiful figure struck the night sky,  with long legs and arms,  veiled in a purple gown that danced and flowed with her.  then,  she blew her trumpet,  the night shook and tore,  the stars of the heavens shone brighter.   fallen and diseased is the earth,  only acts of righteousness shall live on forever.  the earth growls and screams,  dimming,  dying,  duller and duller,   fading forever.

title: Trust

text: a bustle of bloodshed and death.  the virtues of nature,  requesting nothing but givers and receivers of the wreath.  â“take mercy!â” they cry,  but pleas free none,   for no one is spared; no,  he cannot be outdone.  defiance is useless for even the most ruthless.  who are you,  mr.  medbourne? good riddance with your hubris.   â“take mercy!â” they cry,  but pleas free none,  for the will of the almighty cannot be questioned by anyone.   lincoln,  with unification in mind,  appealed to all,  with peace as a holy trust.

title: The Truth In My Thoughts
author: josephine
text: depression really is an interesting thing.  you see people laugh at it,  but they don't really realize how deadly it is.  you see,  depression can come out of nothing.  there are at times that people are actually having fun with friends,  then all of the sudden they can't even smile.  you see,  depression is like seeing a baby,  anything being left by its mother.  you get this rush of dopamine in your brain,  because wow! look at that adorable baby! but when you look deeper down and take a closer look. . .  you see sadness.  and sometimes you live in it.  like a baby kangaroo in its mother's pouch.  some people get medication for their condition.  others can't afford it.  or don't know they even need it.  i'm the third one.  and the second one.  but i think i need to be the first one.  like my brother.  you see my life has been pretty tragic. . .  now some of you are rolling your eyes,  probably thinking,  ''oh yeah? try me.  i bet mines worse!'' well i don't know if mine is or not.  honestly,  if you look at my life from a strangers eyes,  you see a house.  a store,  clothes,  internet,  electricity,  a phone,  running water,  drinking water.  and so much more to be thankful for.  but if you look through my eyes or my friends and relatives,  you see a girl who lost her grandmother,  who was her best friend,  at the age of eleven.  a girl who almost lost her father at the age of twelve.  only to have him live,  but find there are harder days ahead.  with skin cancer,  which was removed,  but before that could happen he would stay in a coma for two weeks,  the hospital for so long his daughter lost count.  then finally,  get an emergency transplant to save his life,  and hopefully do some corrections to the poor life decisions he's made.  only to be later on bit in the but by another condition called diabetes,  to once again remind him of the decisions he's made.  a year later,  you would see the girls second oldest brother be diagnosed with a disease that makes the blood vessels in his hands constrict,  and this seems so little from what happened before,  but it just makes her think,  ''this may just be the beginning. '' oh,  how she wishes she were wrong,  only to be shown she's entirely right.  because a couple years later her oldest brother would be diagnosed with depression.  and she'll realize that the happiest people have the darkest minds.  she'll learn this again when her childhood best friend,  who moved away when she was going into 4th grade,  admits a history of self harm.  and once again when her other childhood best friend,  the one that made them the three musketeers,  admits to domestic violence in his home.  and again when her little cousin,  the one who grew up just a town away,  but seemed to always be only seconds away,  admits to having of thought of suicide. . .  and almost pulled it off,  thankfully that didn't happen thanks to the kid who had been hit by his father so many times he lost count.  but mostly she'll learn that she was right when she's six-teen.  and her mother will tell her that she was diagnosed with at least four types of cancer.  leading to days and nights of no sleep and no focus.  on particular night will always come to mind.  when she woke up to her mother getting sick.  she lays in bed thinking that her dad will hear and help,  because that's his job.  she'll sit there for a couple of minutes until her dad finally comes out.  she thinks,  ''finally,  i can get some rest. '' until her dad walks past her mom to go to the bathroom.  ''okay,  when he gets out he'll help. '' she thinks to herself.  until he comes out and goes back into his bedroom only after saying goodnight to his daughter.  then she'll work up the courage and go out there.  and as she helps her mother,  she'll read a text her mother sent to her father,  saying,  ''help'' you see,  that's when she loses it.  when she goes to school she wont be able to concentrate anymore.  she'll breakdown in front of her english teacher and basketball coaches first,  then her track coach,  and archery coach.  she'll finally tell her mother what's going on.  but when her mother offers to get her help,  she'll say,  ''i don't know. '' because she really doesn't.  she doesn't know if her family can afford it.  and she really doesn't know if she needs it.  but she does know,  deep down,  she should've said yes.  because she's cried more in these past seven months,  than she has in her whole life.  she'll find out the best way to get out her feelings is to write poetry.  but she wont ever let anyone read it.  it'll just sit in a book until she throws it away,  or until she moves it,  or someone finds it.  she'll secretly want someone to find it.  but she'll dread the day.  because even though she know she needs help,  she doesn't know how to ask for it.  or to accept it.  she doesn't know how to explain her feelings.  because when she was little and would cry all the time,  she was told to stop crying and man up.  she thought her feelings were not important.  she doesn't still think that.  instead she doesn't want to tell people because she's afraid they'll see her differently.  not the strong girl she wants to be.  but the weak broken one she is.

title: The Hunter
author: joshua
text: with nothing more than his dog and his weapons by his side.  the hunter is with nature,   he smears mud on his skin and puts twigs in his hair he teaches his dog to be calm.   he hunts until that one day.  when his bow disgraces him and his knife betrays him then he will sleep until he is cold.  like his mother,  the night.

title: Imagination
author: joshua
text: when i close my eyes i picture great lands lands with great pasts and histories with rich traditions and festivals i see wise monarchs,  noble warriors.  and often frightening wizards  i see mysterious forests and sacred deserts i see perilous oceans and majestic cities.  on the tops of the mountains are villainous strongholds,  braved only by courageous lads.   i dream all day until they come.  and tell me to quit and they demand.  i look at our own lives i look and see plains and cities and jungles,  ugly and mundane but great to someone else.

title: After
author: joshua
text: after the sun skims over the peaks,  and the crickets and bugs no longer speak,  after the farmer retires his tools,  and the fish are quiet in the mountain pools,  this is when,  the elders say,  the nightly spirits begin to play.   after their games they have a feast with numerous plates of boiled beast.  and after all have had their fill,  and the sun looms over the eastern hill,  gently and calm they disappear,  longing again for the cool night air.

title: Darkness
author: josie
text: what makes an object real? the human minds ability to see it,  feel it,  smell it,  measure it? a dark room is bigger than a lit one,  the mystery of the dark,  no senses but the ability to hear,  we cannot measure the room,  or objects in it,  or depth,  or demension.  darkness is pit of endlessn possibiliy.   there is a certain freedom in the dark,  a mystery in the absence of light  that allows the mind to wander,  and take a break from reality,  to imagine,  and guess,  and make mistakes,  about the concrete physical realm.   someone once said matter exists  only when the human mind is there to measure it.  darkness is freedom,  darkness is bliss,  darkness is a physical,   mental,   emotional void,  where our emotional minds,  our senses,  our intuitions take over.
